r.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Step 1: Let&rsquo;s the party begin</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Like any other project, you must start your research writing the project with a well laid down plan. In this case, consider what particular area of study and subject matter you want to research. From this broad angle, you then have to streamline your ideas and come up with a more defined narrow scope that will be the focus of your research paper. It is advisable to write down all the ideas you have about that particular subject area as they flood into your mind at this stage.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Step 2: Your choice matters</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The key moment to consider in your research writing project is the choosing of your research topic. Our research paper writing service OZessay.com.au will provide you with detailed tips on how to come up with a good topic. Once the scope is clear, it should be easy to select a relevant topic. Your topic has to have several features including:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The research paper topic has to be clear so that the reader can easily understand what your research paper is all about after the first read.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The research paper topic must be concise. Avoid being too wordy as you are more likely to confuse the reader with many words. Try to say all you need to say as few words as possible and at the same time give a clear picture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The research paper topic must be catchy. A good topic grasps the reader\'s attention and provokes them to read further.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The research paper must have the keywords concerning the concept of discussion. Choose the wording of the topic carefully to ensure that the keywords and the primary concepts of the study are apparent.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Step 3: Turning Sherlock mode on</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">When you are clear about what you want to discuss in your research paper, it is time to carry out some research. Prior preparation helps you to save time so that when you get to carrying out your research you are more strategic. You should use different to assist you in conducting quality research for your paper including; the internet, library, and other forms of mass media. Depending on your kind of research, you may also have to carry out interviews with individuals or groups to provide you the relevant data to include in your research paper.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">From these sources, you will be able to access academic papers, periodicals and other literature that will greatly inform your research paper writing project. From the internet, you can also order research paper at OZessay.com.au, which has been custom made for you after you submit your topic of interest and specifications. You may also buy research paper in similar subject areas to provide with information that will help you develop your research paper.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Step 4: Outlining the main ideas</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Upon completion of your research process, and you have adequate knowledge, you need to organize this information. You will have to go through all the concepts discussed from the various resources you have come across and sieve out the information to get what is relevant to your particular paper. Although everything may seem important, you must understand that your research paper must be of a reasonable length and so you will have to leave out some things.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The best way to do this is to come up with an outline. Choose the most important things that will form the basis of your discussion. Also, at this stage determine what will be discussed first to the last.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Step 5: Drafting, drafting, drafting</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">From the outline, draft the research paper. Drafting involves coming up with the various sections of the research paper. Depending on the specification given by your professors, formulate a skeleton of the research paper. Decide what sub-topics and subsections you will include in your paper. Finally, add the meat to each of the sections. Thus, add all the information you had researched into the right segments.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Step 6: REP: revise, edit, proofread</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Editing and proofreading your research paper involves: ensuring that there is coherency of ideas, spell checking, ensuring that the right academic writing style has been applied to the latter among many other things. Edit your work to ensure the paper rightly communicates what you intended. Our research paper writing service OZessay.com.au will provide you with this service.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Step 7: At last, but not at least</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Most students fail to include a conclusion in their research paper. You must always include a conclusion in your research paper. A conclusion gives an overview of the concepts discussed. In the conclusion, you can give your personal recommendations that you think are relevant from your study. You may also propose further studies that should be done in that particular subject area.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Why it is better to hire a professional writing service</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A professional research paper writing service OZessay.com.au assures you of getting a high-quality research paper. Your paper will be done by highly experienced writers who have written so many quality papers before. Professional writers have vast experience from a variety of fields of study and so they will work on your paper with a multi-disciplinary approach.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">By hiring a professional writing service, you can rest easy knowing that you will always submit your assignment in time. You can order research paper at OZessay.com.au any time of day or night.</p>','Research Paper Writing Guideline','','publish','closed','closed','','custom-research-paper-guideline','','','2017-12-14 13:47:25','2017-12-14 11:47:25','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(94,1,'2016-07-20 20:51:42','2016-07-20 17:51:42','','research-paper-guideline3-v1','','inherit','closed','closed','','research-paper-guideline3-v1','','','2017-12-14 13:47:25','2017-12-14 11:47:25','',93,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/research-paper-guideline3-v1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(95,1,'2016-07-20 20:26:00','2016-07-20 17:26:00','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/argumentative-essay-writing-service\">argumentative essay</a> is a type of essays where&nbsp;students&nbsp;are supposed to investigate, collect and generate information relating to a topic. They should also get evidence and establish a certain position that can be explained in a certain manner. Argumentative essays require extensive research to be conducted, and the arguments in the essay must be reasonable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/argumentative-essay/outline\">ARGUMENTATIVE ESSAY OUTLINE</a></strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;If you are looking for the winning argumentative essay examples here is a great one! Feel free to use it while writing your own essay.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Social Networking: a Boon or a Bane for the Society?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Internet is everywhere you turn. Wherever you go you are sure to find someone using the Internet to do something. At work, school or home, you cannot escape the Internet, and for good reason. The Internet allows you to connect with people in a way, unlike anything you could ever imagine. It doesn\'t matter where someone is located in the world because there is always a way to get ahold of them online. Because of this, social networking has taken the Internet by storm. Wondering whether social networking is worth it? Find out more about whether social networking is a bane or a boon here.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Social Networking: What Is It Exactly?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many people use social networking sites to be able to connect with people who share the same type of interests they do. These dedicated applications and websites were created to give people like you the chance to connect with other users around the globe. Just because you can\'t find someone nearby who shares the same interests as you do that doesn\'t mean there aren\'t plenty of other people out there who do. Social networking is the key to being able to connect with people from around the world who all share the same common interests.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin: 10px auto 10px auto;\" title=\"Social Networking: a Boon or a Bane for the Society?\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/social-networking-essay-sample.jpg\" alt=\"People, connecting each other via social networking\" width=\"650\" height=\"642\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Benefits of Social Networking</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Social networking provides you with a means of connecting with students who are going to college elsewhere and see what they are learning. In fact, you could end up helping each other study for upcoming midterms and learn something new from one another. You never know what one school is teaching over another, but networking gives you the opportunity to learn and grow more.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">One of the biggest benefits to social networking is the fact that you can make new friends and communicate with old friends and family members. Even though you might have lost touch before, you can quickly get back in touch with those that you miss the most. You will also meet a whole new group of people and have the opportunity to form new friendships that could end up lasting a lifetime&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Social networking also gives you the chance to put yourself out there in a positive light. You have the chance to let others know exactly what you have to offer, which can help you out if you are looking for a job and trying to build your network of connections. You can tell people what your skills are and let them know what it is that you are looking to do in life. You never know who someone else might know, which is why it pays to put yourself out there in a positive light and make sure everyone gets the chance to know the real you.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Drawbacks of Social Networking</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">By partaking in social networking sites, you are opening yourself up to cyberbullying. Even though there might be a number of good people out there, there are also a lot of bad people as well. While you might be trying to connect with people who share the same interests, someone else might be out there to tear you down and make you feel like less of an individual. Cyberbullying is huge and isn\'t something that anyone should have to deal with, but it happens all the time.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Social networks can also cause people to feel bad about themselves. You might see someone who is younger than you with more things than what you have, thus causing you to feel insecure about who you are and what you have accomplished in life. Even though you might not know that person\'s history, that doesn\'t make it any less traumatizing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There is also the chance that someone could go online and post an inappropriate picture of you that is taken out of context. What might seem innocent enough soon becomes the main focus of everyone\'s jokes and harassment toward you. You cannot control what other people post online. Even though you can fight it, you end up spending a lot of your time stressing out over what is going to appear online next. That\'s when you have to ask yourself if it is really worth it in the end.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">While no one can say for sure whether social networking is a boon or a bane, it will continue to be a pivotal part of society. Even though one person might benefit from it greatly, another person could end up being hurt by it. There is no way to know which way it is going to go because everyone has their own perception of social networking and the benefits or drawbacks that it brings to the table. Only you can decide whether you think social networking is a boon or a bane.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you need any assistance with your essay writing you can contact our friendly support team and we will gladly help you or you can <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">place on order</a> and our professionals will write a great paper for you.</p>','Argumentative Essay Example. Social Networking: a Boon or a Bane for the Society?','','publish','closed','closed','','custom-essay/argumentative-essay/free-example','','','2017-05-13 13:51:01','2017-05-13 10:51:01','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(96,1,'2016-07-20 20:26:00','2016-07-20 17:26:00','','argumentative-essay-example4-v2','','inherit','closed','closed','','argumentative-essay-example4-v2','','','2017-05-13 13:51:01','2017-05-13 10:51:01','',95,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/argumentative-essay-example4-v2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(97,1,'2016-07-20 18:05:32','2016-07-20 15:05:32','<h3>What Is a Descriptive Essay?</h3>\r\n<p>A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/descriptive-essay\">descriptive essay</a>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;type of an essay that aims to provide a detailed description to&nbsp;the object of the essay, whether it&nbsp;is an emotion or a person, historic event or an object.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-descriptive-essay\">HOW TO WRITE A DESCRIPTIVE ESSAY</a>&nbsp;</strong></h4>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A descriptive essay is usually more focused on a specific topic that is important to a certain audience or targeted group, whereby the writer paints this visual image by appealing to the senses. In other words, it paints a picture with words.</p>\r\n<h2>50 Inspiring Descriptive Essay Topics</h2>\r\n<p>The list of descriptive essay topics that one could think of could fill the stars in the sky. But below, we have compiled some ideas for essay topics based on their level of complexity.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Descriptive Essay Topics on Place</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<style type=\"text/css\"><!--\r\n<g class=\"gr_ gr_261 gr-alert gr_spell gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling ins-del multiReplace\" id=\"261\" data-gr-id=\"261\">td</g> {border: 1px solid #ccc;}br {mso-data-<a href=\"placement:same-cell;}--\">placement:same-cell;}--</a>>\r\n--></style>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Busy Street</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on My Favorite Place</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on New York City</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on London</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on the Beach</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Busy Market Place</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Your Dream House</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on My Bedroom</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Seaworld</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Disneyland</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Times Square</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Descriptive Essay Topics on Events/Holiday</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Memorable Journey</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Rainy Day</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Christmas</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Accident Scene</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Summer Day</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Journey by Train</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Thanksgiving</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Day on an Island</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Moving to other/another City</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Visit to a Hospital</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on French Revolution</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Descriptive Essay Topics on People/Relations</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on My Mother</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on My Best Friend</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Friendship</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Childhood Memories</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Someone You Admire</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on My Brother</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Descriptive Essay Topics on Art</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Sculpture</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Painting</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Picture</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Architecture</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Other Descriptive Essay Topics&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Sports</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Beauty</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Celebrity: Mel Gibson</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Natural Disasters</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Hobbies</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on How to Prepare for an Exam</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Love</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Cognitive Dissonance</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Technology</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Travelling</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Places to Spend a Vacation</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Traditions</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Culture</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Good Day</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on a Place in Nature</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Places to Be Alone</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Nature</li>\r\n<li>Descriptive Essay on Lessons Taught by Life</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Why Is a Professional Writing Service a Good Idea?</h3>\r\n<p>As you can see, there are many topics that teachers may assign or ask you to create that may be somewhat of a challenge to