want for your paper, we will offer suggestions that you can choose from. <strong><a title=\"OzEssay\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/\">OZessay.com.au</a></strong> saves your&nbsp;time you would have used doing the research, and you can use the time doing other activities.</p>','110 Great Research Paper Topics and Ideas','','publish','closed','closed','','research-paper-topics','','','2017-12-14 13:50:40','2017-12-14 11:50:40','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(110,1,'2016-06-29 15:24:41','2016-06-29 12:24:41','','research_paper_topics_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','research_paper_topics_ozessay','','','2017-12-14 13:50:40','2017-12-14 11:50:40','',109,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/research_paper_topics_ozessay.jpg?v=1495606889',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(111,1,'2013-10-30 17:28:07','2013-10-30 15:28:07','<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Introduction to the Research Paper</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Like its name suggests, a research paper necessitates using research in order to come up with something new. Sometimes, this means conducting a factual examination of the information that can be found in the appropriate resources in order to come up with an analysis of a particular issue in a particular field. Other times, this means using the information that can be found in the appropriate resources to craft supporting premises for a particular position on a particular issue in a particular field. However, no matter the purpose of the research paper, it is important to note that it is never as simple and straightforward as regurgitating someone else&rsquo;s research because it demands original thought to go along with what the writer has been reading.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So if you have a&nbsp;research paper that needs to be done, feel free to email us the assignment criteria or <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Writing Help\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">visit our order page to place your order</a></strong> from there. <strong><em>OZessay</em></strong> is the service you can trust!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The Structure of the Research Paper</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"margin: 5px auto; display: block;\" title=\"Research Paper Writing\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/oz-research-paper.jpg\" alt=\"Like most forms of writing, a research paper should begin with an outline to serve as its skeleton, which can be fleshed out piece-by-piece as the writer continues to research and think about their research. Generally speaking, an outline should start with a strong focus so that the rest of the research paper will not meander, but it is important to note that analytical and argumentative research papers tend to do better with different structures.\" width=\"650\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For example, the outline of an <strong>analytical research paper should have these steps</strong>:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1. A statement of the issue that will be analyzed in the research paper, which should come with a description of its context as well as its importance in its field.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2. Research papers based on original research will need a section on how that original research was carried out, thus providing the readers with a way to tell whether it can be trusted or not as well as how much it can be trusted.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">3. The list of the research used for the research paper, which will be used to create the background that readers will need in order to make sense of the analysis. Research chosen for this section should not create a comprehensive overview of the field but remain focused on the parts that are most relevant to the issue.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">4. Once the list of research has been compiled, the outline will then need to describe the general details of the analysis that will be written by using the information collected through said resources. Like the list of research, the information brought up here should be focused on the issue being analyzed so as to maintain both the reader&rsquo;s interest and the research paper&rsquo;s persuasive strength.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">5. Finally, the outline will mention the research paper&rsquo;s conclusion, which should repeat the statement in the opening while also using summarizing the analysis to serve as support. Some research papers provide recommendations for further reading, which should be listed here for ease of use.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In contrast, an <strong>argumentative research paper would benefit from something more along these lines</strong>:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1. Its outline should start with the all-important thesis statement, which should be the focus of the research paper. Bear in mind that the thesis statement of an argumentative research paper should be an opinion about a particular issue in a particular field rather than a factual examination of the research that can be found. However, it should still be made using nothing but the information collected from the appropriate resources.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2. Each supporting premise for the thesis statement should receive its own section in the outline. Said section should include the supporting premise as well as the research that will be used to back it up in the research paper. Furthermore, each section should include the most common counter-arguments to the supporting premise as well as counter-arguments to those counter-arguments to make it as unassailable as possible.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">3. Finally, the outline of an argumentative research paper should have a conclusion that is similar but not quite the same as the outline of an analytical research paper. Its conclusion should still have the thesis statement, but it will need to summarize the supporting premises rather than an analysis that does not exist.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva;\">How to Write a Successful Research Paper</strong></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"margin: 5px auto; display: block;\" title=\"Research Paper Writing Tips\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/research-paper-tips.jpg\" alt=\"To write a successful research paper, you should choose the right topic, research it, make an outline, organize your notes, actually write your paper, edit and proofread it\" width=\"650\" height=\"503\" /></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Here are some further suggestions that can be used to write a successful research paper:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The first step is choosing the right topic. Generally speaking, research paper writers should write about something that interests them since that will provide them with the motivation needed to put in the time and effort needed to ensure excellent results. In fact, research paper writers should not hesitate to change their topic so long as there is enough time remaining for them to make the change without sacrificing the excellence of the results.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The second step is to research the topic using a wide range of resources. Common places to start searching range from the libraries to the academic databases that can be found online. As research paper writers become more and more certain about what they want to write, they should start focusing their readings more and more on a particular issue in order to get the more usefulness out of their efforts.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Once research paper writers have settled on a particular issue and conducted a fair amount of research into their chosen topic, they can start coming up with an outline that will guide their writing. Bear in mind that they should have a thesis statement to serve as a focus by this point in time plus an intended audience so that they know how they should write as well as how much information they should provide to serve as the necessary background. Furthermore, they should continue making changes to their outlines as they continue researching their issue and thinking about their approach.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This is probably the best time to organize the notes, which means sorting the notes for ease of use, coming up with annotations for the information that will be used, and creating a preliminary bibliography that will be revised once the actual writing on the research paper starts.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Once the planning is complete, research paper writers can start on the actual writing. Generally speaking, people like to write from start to finish, but for a research paper, it might be better for them to start with the body before moving onto the conclusion and then the introduction. This is important because completing the body with the analysis and the argument tells them exactly what they should include in the conclusion and the introduction in order to create a coherent document. Once these steps have been completed, a research paper should receive the appropriate citations so that readers will know where to check if they want to confirm the statements made in its paragraphs.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Finally, a research paper should be edited. In part, this means going through the writing to check for spelling errors and grammatical mistakes. However, research paper writers should also have someone read their work to make sure that what makes sense to them makes sense to readers as well. A research paper cannot be considered complete without incorporating the corrections from the editing process, so much so that significant rewrites should have their own editing processes.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Useful Services For Writing a Research Paper</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There are a number of useful resources for research paper writers. For example, both instructors and librarians can point them to the right resources, while their friends can make excellent proofreaders. Furthermore, examples of research papers can be found throughout the Internet, which can tell them more about what they should and should not do when writing their research papers.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">However, if they are interested in assistance with research topics on their chosen topics, there are few options that are as useful as research paper writing services, which can provide them with a custom-made example to serve as a guide for their own efforts. While guidelines are genuinely useful for those seeking to write a research paper, seeing the finished product can bring them together like nothing else for people who are struggling with their research papers.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Research Papers by OZessay</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We are proud to offer the best research papers in the academic services industry. Our academic experience and a pool of top quality writers allow us to work effectively on research papers of all kinds. All our writers are selected on the basis of their background as well as their research/writing skills. For example, if the writer specializes in writing MA or MSc level research papers, he or she will be dealing only with this type of assignments. This allows us to concentrate on specific assignments and build up unparalleled expertise in the sphere.&nbsp;<a title=\"Writing Help\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">Click here to order a Research Paper!</a></p>','Research Paper: How to Write a Winning One with a Proper Structure','','publish','closed','closed','','research-paper','','','2017-05-17 10:00:36','2017-05-17 07:00:36','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(112,1,'2013-10-30 17:28:07','2