our case, and instead of finding a guided essay writing tips, you find something like Naplan writing marking guide or cursive writing guide, this time you are at the right place. Our professional writers have prepared a detailed information in the form of a guide - writing an essay will become much more easier if you read the tips below. So, the guided writing tips from our experts include:</p>\r\n<p>1. Choose a topic or get an idea about the one you have been provided: Get an idea about the topic you have and what points to include. The topic can either be a general overview or a specific one. If it\'s specific, ensure that the analysis is precise and only about that specific point, for a general overview topic like `FOOD`, you can subdivide into certain subtopics. The subtopics to include can be `vegetables` or fruits`.</p>\r\n<p>2. Organize your ideas: Organize on how you will write your ideas in the essay, however, the structure on how you will organize the ideas or point can change according to the flow of the essay. You can choose to put it down in a diagram to get a clear overview on how your points will be detailed.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create a thesis statement: After getting an idea or point to put forth in your essay, you can now write a thesis statement. The thesis statement informs the reader what the essay is all about and what you as a writer have provided in the essay. Your thesis point will be in two main parts, that is the topic and the point of the essay. On the point of the essay part of the thesis, the ideas or points to include depends on the size of the essay, however, the points should be in summary form and they should, therefore, be few. Once you are comfortable with your thesis and you have all the points to include in the essay, you can move to the next step.</p>\r\n<p>4. Write the body: In this part, you will describe, explain and dispute your topic in a detailed manner. Each idea will be now in paragraphs, which translate to four or five paragraphs if you had four or five ideas. Start by summarizing each idea in sentence form, then write the supporting ideas and clearly elaborate them. Then after explaining each of the main ideas, move on to the next step.</p>\r\n<p>5. Always ensure you have a good introduction and conclusion. On the introductory part, always ensure it grabs the attention of the reader. That can be done by writing the points that will make the reader seek more information in your essay and continue with another two more inviting sentences.</p>\r\n<p>6. Add the final touches: that includes ensuring that the essay is in the correct format as well as the formatting is properly followed. Also read out your essay to ensure that the grammar is good.</p>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"../../five-paragraph-essay\">FIVE-PARAGRAPH ESSAY</a></h4>\r\n<p>The above essay writing tips will be quite beneficial for you to have a clear and an excellent essay. The above tips can be as well used as an academic writing guide. That is because in the course work the same tips are helpful.</p>','Academic Writing Guide: 6 Tips to Write Essays Like an Expert','','publish','closed','closed','','writing-guide','','','2017-05-23 13:31:56','2017-05-23 10:31:56','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(128,1,'2013-10-29 14:22:20','2013-10-29 12:22:20','','academic_writing_guide_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','academic_writing_guide_ozessay','','','2017-05-23 13:31:56','2017-05-23 10:31:56','',127,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/academic_writing_guide_ozessay.jpg?v=1495535504',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(129,1,'2010-07-13 11:20:36','2010-07-13 08:20:36','<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">Term Paper</h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Term papers get a bad rap for being brain-sucking stumbling blocks a student hits on the way to completion of their course. What&rsquo;s unfortunate is that students don&rsquo;t see the things that make term papers important (and even pleasurable) to write.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Advantages of the Term Papers\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/term-paper-advantages.jpg\" alt=\"Term papers help bring light to new and unexplored subjects, they help us form ideas and opinions, ultimately helping one draw conclusions about themselves and the world. Getting an A on a term paper will make a significant impact on the final course mark&mdash;sometimes up to 50% of the course. And remember, writing doesn&rsquo;t have to be a chore if you delegate the work to a professional.\" width=\"650\" height=\"226\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Term paper writing services\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/term-paper-writing-services\">Ordering a paper from an online service</a></strong> of professional writers is a proven way to academic success. <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">Click here to place your order right now!</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What follows covers all of the elements of a term paper, from designing the outline to looking into professional writers who can help you write an A+ paper when you don&rsquo;t have the time to complete one that is up to your high standards.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Structure and Outline of a term paper</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This is the critical step in the term paper writing process. <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Term Paper Outline\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/term-paper-outline-become-super-organized\">A paper can only be as good as its outline.</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Key Hole Design is the most popular structure for essay, whereby the writer leads with an introductory first paragraph, followed by the essay body. The introduction contains a thesis statement and the body paragraphs present the arguments and supporting evidence that are set to prove the thesis.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As you do your research, take the time to revisit your outline often. You may find some ideas need more information to flesh them out and others you will find are dead ends. Keeping in touch with your outline during the research phase will help keep you on track and in line with your paper&rsquo;s purpose.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Each time you make a significant edit to your outline, test each point you add for its clarity, and test each structural change to see if the paper still makes a convincing case toward its conclusion. The final outline should cover all the main points that were posed in the thesis statement.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Once you have a detailed outline, the next step is to organize your information in a way that it clearly proves your thesis through facts, quotes and empirical evidence. To accomplish that, you must back up the facts and explain all of your conclusions drawn from facts. Organize the paper by using each body paragraph to state, verify and explain one fact that supports the thesis.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">What is the purpose of a term paper?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As a writer, you should be aiming to expand the reader&rsquo;s knowledge beyond that which they would glean from the source material. The typical term paper takes on the ultimate purpose to:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Research and investigate a topic deeply, using trustworthy materials.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Synthesize information from several sources to uncover patterns and relationships where they weren&rsquo;t previously seen.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Organize materials from many sources into one curated body of writing.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Analyze the work by critiquing the evidence, validity, logic, and flaws behind their ideas and arguments.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Clarify to make challenging or confusing material understandable for even a layman.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examine the topic in another context, or apply the learning to another place or time for a broader perspective.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Edit voraciously for fluff that does not add to the core idea.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adopt a point of view and show that evidence weighs heavier on one side in a controversial issue.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Term paper writing tips</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">General tips</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1.An average length (10-20 pages) should take about one month to adequately collect the materials and lay them out in a finished paper.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2.Create a schedule to help you keep track of time: list the days you have left and the time during the day you&rsquo;ll be able to work. Even if you have two weeks until the due date, you may be surprised at home few hours you have free.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">3.Get a library card. There is no way to do the kind of deep research necessary for a term paper just through online sources.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">4.Limit yourself to having only 10-15% of your finished paper made of quotations.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">5.Use the correct dictionary, as requested by your professor&mdash;there is a difference!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">6.Read drafts aloud to catch awkward phrasing. If you stumble on something while reading, rework it.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Thesis statement tips</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1.Keep it simple and as specific as possible.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2.Take your thesis to your professor or supervisor for their opinion.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Taking notes</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1.Use a color or index card system to code your paper research notes. Do a quick Google search and choose a research coding system that seems right for you.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2.Take note of ever source you pull, including the author&rsquo;s name, the publication date and the page numbers you used. Even if you just took away one little note.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Outline</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1.Set up the wording of your thesis statement carefully. Certain wording could drastically change where you can go with your research. Example: To theorize that Othello is a play about love and jealousy is far too broad of a subject and will overwhelm you with research sources and previous essays on the subject.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2.For each point you make in the body, make about three points proving its validity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">3.Write your first draft close to the outline but as freely as possible. Don&rsquo;t get bogged down by thinking of the reader&rsquo;s perspective yet.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">The dos and don&rsquo;ts of term paper writing</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Do\'s and Don\'ts of Term Paper Writing\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/term-paper-writing-tips.jpg\" alt=\"When you write your term paper you should: start writing as early as possible, try to explain the ideas in your own words, explore your own ideas and insights through writing, but avoid getting too stylistic and use the process to clarify your own ideas and understand the world around you. But you should not: budget too little time for editing, include anything that doesn&rsquo;t directly answer to the thesis statement, cite Wikipedia as a source, and overshoot the word count to try to earn more points\" width=\"650\" height=\"496\" /></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Where can one find a term paper writer?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The process to hire a term paper writer looks like this:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1.Start by filling out an order form</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2.Submit your professor&rsquo;s instructions and any material you would like to add to direct the project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">3.Get assigned a writer&mdash;sometimes the writer is hand-picked by the service so as to make a good match. Or the assignment is submitted to an open pool of writers to be picked up by the next available writer.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">4.Agree to some terms and submit payment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">5.Receive a page that outlines your order and serves as an agreement between you and your writer that the work will be done to you specifications in the time allotted.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">6.Communicate with your writer through an online messaging service. If your writer has any questions along the way, this is how they will submit those queries. Keep an eye on your inbox so you can keep everything moving smoothly and efficiently.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">7.Wait for the paper to be delivered by the deadline you specified.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">8.Request revisions if necessary. Sometimes those revisions will incur an additional cost.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Why is it better to use term paper writing services?</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Confidential service</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">You are hiring a writer not only to produce your work but to back away from the work once it&rsquo;s handed over. They will not steal or use your paper under their own name and they will not disclose their hand in its creation. A good online paper writing service will provide non-disclosure agreements to confirm the understanding of this by both parties.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Scope of work</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Most term paper writing services can help you write nearly anything: biographies, memoirs, family or corporate histories, website copy, fiction, scripts and blogs.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Reasonable prices</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Term paper writers charge by the word and a good writer won&rsquo;t add fluff just to increase their payout. If you are on a budget, you can have a writer do the majority of the research and layout while you polish and edit the work.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Speedy service</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Professional writers are being paid to focus solely on the work and have it done by a certain deadline. You can rest assured that you won&rsquo;t be losing any points for punctuality.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva;\"><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">YOU CAN PLACE YOUR ORDER HERE!</a></strong></p>','How to Write a Term Paper: Writing Outline and Term Paper Proposal','','publish','closed','closed','','writing-term-paper','','','2017-05-16 15:18:05','2017-05-16 12:18:05','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(130,1,'2010-07-13 11:20:36','2010-07-13 08:20:36','','how_to_write_a_term_paper_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','how_to_write_a_term_paper_ozessay','','','2017-05-16 15:18:05','2017-05-16 12:18:05','',129,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/how_to_write_a_term_paper_ozessay.jpg?v=1495547433',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(131,1,'2010-07-13 11:17:27','2010-07-13 08:17:27','<p>Most of our long standing clients had started out by placing one tentative order with us but upon receiving the completed work, they have joined the multitude of our satisfied customer 