-30 11:46:44','<blockquote> <q>Descriptive essay writing is a process of depicting some place, event, person, painting, etc. Here is a great list of words used to describe works of art. </q> </blockquote><h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What Is a Descriptive Essay?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing a descriptive essay can be likened to painting a picture, creating a piece of music, creating a sculpture with just words. After reading your essay your reader should have a vivid and clear picture of the portrayed object, and the more colorful the image is, the better you have managed to reach your readers&rsquo; minds and the better you have mastered descriptive essay writing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin: 10px auto 10px auto;\" title=\"Descriptive Essay Definition\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/descriptive-essay-definition.png\" alt=\"In your descriptive essay you may depict a place, person, a piece of music, some architecture or anything that is significant to you and will be interesting to your reader\" width=\"750\" height=\"257\" /></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\">Learn: <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-descriptive-essay\">How to Write a Descriptive Essay</a></h4>\r\n<h4>Choose a topic for your descriptive essay: <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/custom-essay/descriptive-essay/topics-and-ideas\">50 Inspiring Descriptive Essay Topics</a></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you feel unsure how to write your descriptive essay, you can always&nbsp;ask for professional assistance&nbsp;from our writers. Feel free to contact us and we will come up with a top-notch product that exceeds your expectations. Once you are ready, feel free to request assistance via chat, phone or email.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Purpose of the Descriptive Essay</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As any other essay types, descriptive essay writing is meant to, first of all, facilitate your writing and critical thinking skills. However, with descriptive essay writing this isn&rsquo;t just the case: you need to observe the object, note what makes it unique, different, notable; if you are writing about a piece of music you will need to speak about things like melody, beat, rhythm, lyrics, tempo, harmony, general message etc. All these tasks require a lot of observation skills, ability to observe, notice, analyze and then verbalize one&rsquo;s feelings and put them on paper. Summing up, a descriptive essay is a piece of writing that bridges your sensory perception with your writing skills.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Descriptive Essay Structure</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Descriptive Essays are no different in terms of structure than regular Five Paragraph Essays. This means that they should consist of the introductory paragraph, two to three body paragraphs and the concluding paragraph. The introduction should contain the main essay idea and serve as an attention getter to the reader. Body paragraphs break the main idea into smaller subtopics and dwell on them in greater detail. Each body paragraph should consist of about 6-7 sentences. The final part of any essay is the conclusion. Typically it echoes ideas presented in the introduction and brings them to a logical ending. If your essay is required to be different structurally, stick to the instructions from your school. If, however, you need to write a classical descriptive essay, please refer to <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"How to Structure Your Essay\" href=\"../../essay-structure\">this article</a>.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Tips on Descriptive Essay Writing</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">When creating a description essay writers typically use two approaches:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin: 10px auto 10px auto;\" title=\"Approaches to a Descriptive Essay Writing\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/descriptive-essay-types.png\" alt=\"Typically there are two approaches used in the descriptive essay writing: objective and subjective\" width=\"750\" height=\"333\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Objective Description</strong> &ndash; used to describe physical objects, technical things or present reporting. It is a direct, real to life description of something. The author is providing the reader with facts. Objective description lacks emotions and feelings. It does not give the reader an idea of writer&rsquo;s attitude to the object (just like in an informative essay).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Subjective</strong> (impressionistic) &ndash; is the opposite of the objective approach. The reader will see the picture with your eyes and share the feelings and emotions that the described object evokes in the author.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Unlike objective description, this approach employs all the senses to convey the desirable meaning and achieve the necessary effect. You will share your view and attitude towards the presented subject (much like in a <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"How to Write a Personal Essay?\" href=\"../../personal-experience-essay\">personal essay</a>). This type of description tends to be very sensual, emotional and thoughtful.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">How to Write Descriptive Essays on Paintings</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Describing paintings, pieces of music and architecture are the most typical assignments students get. In order to ease up the writing process, we suggest that whenever a&nbsp;painting is described, the description could take a specific pattern:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li>What is the title of the painting?</li>\r\n<li>Who is the author?</li>\r\n<li>When was this painting created? What historical context has it been placed in? (e.g. revolution, personal conflict, marriage, travel etc.) What inspired the artist to create it?</li>\r\n<li>What art movement and epoch does it belong to? (e.g. impressionism, modernism, classicism, purism, cubism etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Is the painting figurative or abstract? Describe what you see or how the picture makes you feel.</li>\r\n<li>Describe material the artist used to create the picture (oil, coal, pencil, watercolor etc).</li>\r\n<li>Describe form, lines, shapes, colors, values, and textures.</li>\r\n<li>Speak of proportions, balance, emphasis, rhythm, and pattern. Describe how the artist used these elements to attain a certain artistic effect.</li>\r\n<li>Describe what is happening in the picture.</li>\r\n<li>State what you think of the painting. Do you like or dislike it?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We recommend that you write down responses on a separate sheet of paper and then organize them in a <strong>full-scale essay</strong> according to the pattern mentioned above. In wording your responses, you might need to use some art-specific words (see Table 1):</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Table 1. Words used to describe works of art</h3>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border: 1px solid #708090; width: 646px; float: left;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>abstract</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">abstract art expresses the artist&rsquo;s ideas or feelings rather than showing the exact appearance of people or things</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>accessible</td>\r\n<td>accessible art, music, literature etc is easy to understand and enjoy</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>aesthetic</td>\r\n<td>relating to beauty or to the study of the principles of beauty, especially in art</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>artistic</td>\r\n<td>relating to any form of art, including painting, music, literature, acting, and dancing</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>arty-crafty</td>\r\n<td>made by someone who enjoys creating and decorating things themselves, but who you think lacks a skill</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>avant-garde</td>\r\n<td>avant-garde music, art etc is very modern and may shock people because it is so different from what has gone before</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>baroque</td>\r\n<td>relating to the very detailed style of art, building, or music that was popular in Europe in the 17th and early 18th centuries</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>cubist</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">relating to an early 20th-century style of painting in which the artist paints several different views of a person or object in a single painting, usually using straight lines</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>evocative</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">an evocative work of art expresses something very clearly and makes you have a strong reaction to it</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>figurative</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">figurative art represents people, objects, and scenes, rather than representing feelings or ideas as abstract art does</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>folk</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">folk art, traditions, stories etc were developed by people in a particular region and have become traditional there</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>formal</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">relating to the form or structure of something such as a piece of writing, art, or music</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>freehand</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">drawn without using a ruler or other equipment</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Gothic</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">Gothic styles of building and art were common in Europe between the 12th and 15th centuries</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>grandiose</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">designed to look very impressive, but really looking artificial or silly</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>mature</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">the mature work of an artist, writer etc is produced when they are no longer young and have developed their skill to a high level</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>minimalist</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">relating to minimalism</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>monochrome</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">using different shades of a single colour</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>naturalistic</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">a naturalistic painting, novel etc shows people and things as they are in real life</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>pictorial</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">consisting of pictures</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>pre-Raphaelite</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">typical of a style of art popular in late 19th century England that used a lot of detail and bright colours and showed a very romanticized view of life</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>pure</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">a pure form of art does not have any practical purpose, such as selling something</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>representational</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">representational paintings and other works of art show things as they really are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Romantic</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">relating to the style of literature, art, and music known as romanticism</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>satirical</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">satirical writing or art uses humour to criticize people or things and make them seem silly</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>surrealistic</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">connected with surrealism</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>stylized</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">in a style that is artificial rather than realistic (=like life)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>stereoscopic</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">a stereoscopic picture is designed so that when you look at it through a special piece of equipment, it looks solid and real</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>seminal</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">a seminal piece of writing or music is new and different and influences other literature or music that comes after it</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>untitled</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">an untitled poem, book, painting etc has not been given a title</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br /><br /></p>','Descriptive Essay: Fab Tips on How to Write a Good One with OZessay','','publish','closed','closed','','descriptive-essay','','','2017-05-25 10:12:18','2017-05-25 07:12:18','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(176,1,'2013-10-30 13:46:44','2013-10-30 11:46:44','','descriptive_essay_writing_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','descriptive_essay_writing_ozessay','','','2017-05-25 10:12:18','2017-05-25 07:12:18','',175,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/descriptive_essay_writing_ozessay.jpg?v=1495696645',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(177,1,'2013-10-30 16:44:38','2013-10-30 14:44:38','<blockquote> <q>A description essay depicts some place, event, or person in an interesting way for the reader.</q> </blockquote><p style=\"text-align: left;\">If your task is to produce a description essay, you are no more a writer; you turn into a mighty painter. The pen becomes your magic paintbrush with which you paint images of the described subject in the minds of the reader.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In your description essay, you may depict some place, event, and person, anything that is significant to you and will be interesting to the readers. After reading your essay the reader should have a vivid and clear picture of the portrayed object.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Need an idea to write a description essay? Here is a list of 50 descriptive essay topic</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/custom-essay/descriptive-essay/topics-and-ideas\">50 Inspiring Descriptive Essay Topics</a></h4>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Writers use one of the two methods of description:</strong></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">1. They turn for an&nbsp;<em>objective description</em> to describe physical objects, technical things or present reporting. It is a direct, real to life description of something. The author is inclined to provide the reader with the facts. Objective description lacks emotions and feelings. It does not give the reader an idea of writer&rsquo;s attitude to the object (just like in an informative essay).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2. <em>Subjective</em> (impressionistic) is quite the opposite. The reader will see the picture with your eyes and you are to evoke strong feelings in his mind. Unlike objective description, it employs all the senses to convey the desirable meaning and achieve the necessary effect. You will share your view on the presented subject (much like in a personal essay). This type of description tends to be very sensual, emotional and thoughtful.</p>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\">Read more: <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-descriptive-essay\">How to Write a Descriptive Essay</a></h4>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>A descriptive essay must be:<br /></strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bright</li>\r\n<li>Sensual</li>\r\n<li>Reminiscent</li>\r\n<li>Gripping</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>How do you achieve it?<br /></strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Focus on your feelings</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vary lexical and syntactical means</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Follow chronological order of your description</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Describe your 5 senses: sight, smell, hearing, taste, and touch</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Share your associations with the described senses</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Choose examples with care</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you have a descriptive essay to write and don\'t still don\'t know how to do it, OzEssay.com.au is ready to provide academic assistance to meet your goals. Since 2008 we have successfully completed hundreds of description essays and our customers come back to use for me. Please feel free to use the&nbsp;<strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"../../order\">order</a></strong>&nbsp;page or email your instructions at&nbsp;<strong>support@ozessay.com.au</strong>&nbsp;for review.</p>','Descriptive Essay: Key Methods of Describing Things from OZessay','','publish','closed','closed','','description-essay','','','2017-05-17 11:48:09','2017-05-17 08:48:09','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(178,1,'2013-10-30 16:44:38','2013-10-30 14:44:38','','description-essay3-v2','','inherit','closed','closed','','description-essay3-v2','','','2017-05-17 11:48:09','2017-05-17 08:48:09','',177,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/description-essay3-v2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(179,1,'2013-10-29 14:40:33','2013-10-29 12:40:33','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For many students, English essay writing feels like slaying a beast. This information serves as instruction as to how to write an English essay. Using a guideline, like the traditional five-paragraph English essay structure, is a great start and allows for the process of English essay writing to be less daunting. By following the four main steps to English essay writing, the final product will be concise, convincing and informative.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Rough Draft</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Sometimes described as \"laying down the bones,\" the initial step in the English essay structure does not involve much actual writing. This is the opportunity to identify the focus and define the purpose of the essay. Many essays address similar topics, so attempt to identify an original approach to the topic. First, become an expert on the topic through research, then decide whether the goal is to inform the readers, to persuade them into action or to narrate a story. Write down every idea at this point and let them flow.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Crafting the Introduction</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Beginning the paper with an interesting anecdote, statistic or quotation is the best way to grab the reader\'s attention. Continue with the thesis and a summation of the essay\'s three main points. The thesis is the overarching idea that you are communicating to the readers, stated in one concise sentence. It typically expresses an idea that is new and interesting to the audience. For example, \"summer weather heats up\" isn\'t a great thesis, since not many would dispute it and it seems like common knowledge, while \"summer weather is heating up more with each passing year\" is both fresh and arguable. Avoid phrases like, \"I\'m going to tell you&hellip;\" or \"This essay is about&hellip;.\" English essay writing is most effective when done in third person.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Creating the Body and Conclusion</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Body paragraphs for each main point follow the introduction. It is customary to begin with the second strongest argument. The point should be stated in the first or second sentence and immediately followed with supporting details and evidence. Refer back to the stated topic to ensure that the content is not off-topic. Avoid \"I believe\" or \"I think\" opinion statements and create confident sentences. Conclude with your strongest point for impact and so that it sticks with readers. In the conclusion, restate the thesis and summarize without repeating it exactly. Wrap up with a powerful quotation or call to action that encourages your reader to be inspired and act.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Time to Edit</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Let the paper rest for a while before you begin editing if you have the time. Editing is the polishing of a rough draft by checking the English essay structure and general flow of the sentences. Consider the word choices made and the transitions between paragraphs and ideas. Read the essay aloud to evaluate sentence length and flow. Remove words used only to impress. Each word should have a specific value. Check for smooth transitions from one idea to another.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Proofreading Made Easy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">When editing is complete, it is time for a detailed check for spelling, grammar, capitalization and punctuation errors. Never rely on the spell-check tool in your word-processing program, as they do not evaluate context. The best way to check spelling is to read the essay backwards from the last word to the first word. By following this tip, your eyes review what is written, rather than what is expected. Choose a clear 12-point font that is easy to read and has clean lines, like Arial.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many students wonder how to write an English essay. Here we give you a few simple tools. If, however, you do need help with essay writing, OZessay is the service that is willing to assist you in any academic situation. Please feel free to contact our support team at <a href=\"mailto:support@ozessay.com.au\">support@ozessay.com.au</a>&nbsp;or place your order via the order page.</p>','Strategies for Effective English Essay Writing','','publish','closed','closed','','english-essay','','','2017-05-17 12:57:39','2017-05-17 09:57:39','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(180,1,'2013-10-29 14:40:33','2013-10-29 12:40:33','','writing-an-english-essay-v1','','inherit','closed','closed','','writing-an-english-essay-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:57:39','2017-05-17 09:57:39','',179,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/writing-an-english-essay-v1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(181,1,'2013-10-30 16:25:22','2013-10-30 14:25:22','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">When you write a literature essay, you need to combine your abilities in writing critical comparison and analytical essays. You are expected to understand the author&rsquo;s point of view and explain it to the reader. You are also required to analyze the language tools the author has used in his writing. You need to be able to describe the content of the writing through key literature terms such as irony, satire, character, metaphor, epithet etc.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In order to evaluate the literature, you need to use what is termed as &ldquo;close reading.&rdquo; This suggests that you should be reading with the intension of identifying different levels of meanings within the text.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In getting prepared to write your English literature essay, you need to plan the essay and its structure. The research question as well as the thesis statement should be included in the introduction. Each paragraph in the body of the essay should be dedicated to discussing each point so that your essay will be easy to follow.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Knowing how to write an English essay will help you to achieve success in your writing; sticking to a proper essay structure will add 10-15% to your grade.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Include quotations and references in correct format as per the style guide you are prescribed to follow and avoid the use of long quotations. The basic rule is to limit quotes to no more than three lines. Use the conclusion to summarize the thesis statement and highlight the important issued discussed. Also emphasis why the topic discussed is of important in terms of broader and more critical context.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-decoration: none; text-align: left;\"><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Term paper writing services\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/term-paper-writing-services\">Ordering a paper from an online service</a>&nbsp;of professional writers is a proven way to academic success.&nbsp;</p>','English Literature','','publish','closed','closed','','english-literature','','','2017-05-16 15:19:18','2017-05-16 12:19:18','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(182,1,'2013-10-30 16:25:22','2013-10-30 14:25:22','','english_literature-v1','','inherit','closed','closed','','english_literature-v1','','','2017-05-16 15:19:18','2017-05-16 12:19:18','',181,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/english_literature-v1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(183,1,'2014-01-31 09:44:56','2014-01-31 07:44:56','<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing Winning Essay Papers</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An academic essay attempts to convince readers and essay markers of an idea based upon evidence. An academic essay ought to answer a query or task. It must have a thesis statement (reply to the concern) along with an argument. It should aim to discuss or present something: create a thesis through a set of carefully related points by evidence and reasoning. An academic essay must include pertinent examples, supporting information and evidence from credible sources or academic texts. If you need to have your essay written by professionals - <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">place your order here!</a></strong></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Key steps in creating an essay</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Although there`re some primary steps to composing an academic paper, essay writing isn\'t a linear procedure. You may work through various stages a couple of times in the duration of crafting an essay. For instance, you may return to the note taking and reading stage if you identify another helpful text, or probably to re-read to find specific information.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Start early</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">You cannot write an effective essay except if you give yourself sufficient time to think, read, research, and write. Don\'t leave it or procrastinate until the very last minute; get started as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Determine the question and evaluate the task.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ensure that you understand precisely what the question demands you to do.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Identify the crucial words (like analyzing or discuss) and make clear the approach you\'re required to take.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Write an initial essay plan</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Your beginning stage for an essay is the initial reaction to the question or topic. This reaction is based upon what you presently know. Even so, this is only the beginning point. After this, you need to research, query your response and discover some answers.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Researching your argumentative essay topics</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An attribute of many persuasive essay papers is that it relies on the work of other researchers and writers. Therefore, researching and reading are keys to essay writing. By researching you will get the evidence and knowledge which will enable you to address the essay question</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Organizing Your Ideas</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Start organizing your ideas and research into an answer.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">After you have investigated and your thoughts are more developed, generate a subsequent essay plan. It\'ll help you figure out how to address the question/topic and how the paper will be organized. Determine a possible answer to the topic/question (with regards to the research you\'ve done).</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Decide on the evidence/information you\'ll use to address the question</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Take a look at your notes and select examples to offer evidence in supporting your answer</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Choose which points you\'ll discuss, and their order</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Thinking it through</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Essay writing demands both critical and creative thinking.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Creative thinking motivates you to expand your ideas. Consider techniques like mind mapping or brainstorming.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Critical thinking stimulates you to filter the scope or focus of your ideas (for instance, asking why a case in point is vital to your argument).</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your essay ought to be balanced: which is, it should contain an array of information and opinions from several authors that examine the pertinent aspects and key arguments and of a specific topic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing your essay paper</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Your initial draft is not going to be your final piece; visualize it as a raw material you\'ll refine through re-drafting and editing. Once you have a draft, you may work on crafting well.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Structuring the essay</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Structuring your paper in the most powerful way to convey your ideas/points and address the question is also important.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Essay paragraph</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Each section of your research paper should contain:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>A topic sentence</strong> which states the controlling or central idea</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Supporting sentences</strong> to develop and explain the point you`re making</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Evidence.</strong> Your main point must be supported by pertinent evidence from your readings.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Analysis.</strong> Never leave the facts hanging there - interpret and analyze it! Touch upon the implication/impact/significance and sign off the last part with a critical summary you\'ve pulled from the evidence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Referencing</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">All academic essays should have references. Referencing protects against plagiarism, a severe academic offense. Ensure that you are acquainted with the referencing styles your school or faculty requires.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Editing and proofreading</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The last thing you must do is to edit and proofread your <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Persuasive Essay Topics\" href=\"../../how-to-write-a-persuasive-essay\">persuasive essay topics</a></strong> to ensure there is no spelling, grammar issues and to fine-tune your essay. Should you require essay writing assistance, we are always ready to help. Email our customer support at <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Support\" href=\"mailto:support@ozessay.com.au\">support@ozessay.com.au</a></strong>&nbsp;in case you need more information, or simply place your order via <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Order Page\" href=\"../../order\">our order page</a></strong>.</p>','Writing a Winning Essay Topic for Your Paper | OZessay.com.au','','publish','closed','closed','','essay-topic','','','2017-05-16 14:22:31','2017-05-16 11:22:31','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(184,1,'2014-01-31 09:44:56','2014-01-31 07:44:56','','writing_an_essay_topic_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','writing_an_essay_topic_ozessay','','','2017-05-16 14:22:31','2017-05-16 11:22:31','',183,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/writing_an_essay_topic_ozessay.jpg?v=1495706569',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(185,1,'2013-10-30 13:56:10','2013-10-30 11:56:10','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An expository essay is a type of essay writing that involves <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"../../expository-essay\">choosing a topic&nbsp;for an expository essay</a></strong>, substantiating the idea with facts, and presenting a written argument that is clear and compelling.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Expository essays are one of the best-known essay types that are typically written with a balanced view. As the writer would need to carefully examine both sides of an issue to formulate a thesis or main idea, to write an effective expository essay, this particular format is heavily utilized for tests and exams. When writing an expository essay, the student may use an analytical approach, contrast and compare technique, or use cause and effect to give weight to an idea.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As with most types of essays, the expository essay structure should follow a general guideline. The following steps illustrate how an expository essay should be outlined:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A strong thesis statement that tells the reader about the main idea of the essay.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Several paragraphs that form the body of the essay and include information that substantiates, or supports, the main idea stated in the thesis.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A solid conclusion that takes the supporting information used throughout the essay, sums it all up and ends by reinforcing the thesis statement.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">While it is important to follow the general outline for a well-structured expository essay, it is also important to pay attention to certain details. When writing the body of the essay, the writer should be aware of how transitions are used between paragraphs. Transitions could be considered the connective thread of the expository essay, words and grammatical phrases that pull the essay together. Transitional phrases often include the use of adverbs or an opening sentence that ties into the concluding statement of the previous paragraph.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing an expository essay isn\'t all about following the rules, however! A writer also has a lot of latitudes to be very creative during the writing process, too. Yes, expository essays are based on supporting facts and composing an effective essay is, in itself, a bit technical. Yet, the writer can infuse the essay with their individual voice with wording. This can be tricky because going too far with the creativity carries the risk of distracting the reader from the main point of what the expositor essay writer is trying to convey.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">When writing the conclusion of an expository essay, the writer has the best chance of leaving the strongest impression on the reader. Many students utilize a strategy that sums up the entire essay by composing sentences that readdress the points made in the body of the essay. This can be an effective strategy when the wording is concise and compelling.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Once students began to understand the basics of how to write an expository essay, they gain an invaluable tool for creating effective arguments, a beneficial attribute that can last a lifetime. Expository essays are a wonderful way to learn how to introduce a powerful idea, explain why it matters, and convincing the world that your perspective does, in fact, matter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Are you a student or writer that has need of an expository essay? Are you looking to improve your grades, apply for school, or impress your boss? OZessay is a 24/7 service that provides intelligent and original essays when you need it. Our top talent team is comprised of writers with advanced degrees and steadfast dedication to our clients. <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"../../order\">Place your order</a></strong> today and get started on creating a better tomorrow!</p>','Expository Essay: How to Write and Structure an Expository Essay','','publish','closed','closed','','expository-essay','','','2017-05-16 14:25:23','2017-05-16 11:25:23','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(186,1,'2013-10-30 13:56:10','2013-10-30 11:56:10','','expository-essay-writing-v2','','inherit','closed','closed','','expository-essay-writing-v2','','','2017-05-16 14:25:23','2017-05-16 11:25:23','',185,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/expository-essay-writing-v2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(187,1,'2014-02-13 12:44:20','2014-02-13 10:44:20','<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">What Is a Five-Paragraph Essay?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A five-paragraph essay is the basic essay form, consisting of an introduction, three body paragraphs, and a conclusion. If your assignment doesn&rsquo;t tell you specifically how to write an essay you need to come up with, it is implied that you are expected to write a 5 paragraph essay. This staple essay is most often found in high-school and junior college years, and as an academic complexity of studies goes up, essay <a title=\"Assignment Writing Help \" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/assignment-writing-help\">writing assignments</a> get more sophisticated too.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Why are five paragraph essays important?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">It has been conventionally agreed that a five paragraph essay is a basic essay format. Its <a href=\"../../five-paragraph-essay/outline\">simple structure</a> allows students to practice effective and organized writing by following an invariant logical pattern, which eventually results in increased ability to explain a problem or a phenomenon. The ability to write logically following a set essay format will on later stages evolve in clear and logical research and academic writing. Therefore the skills for writing a five-paragraph essay are essential for your academic success.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;Our writers guarantee the premium quality content, complete reference, and zero plagiarism.&nbsp;<a title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">Place your order here</a>&nbsp;and enjoy the result!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">What is the basic essay structure?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Generally speaking, five paragraph essays have a fixed structure. As its name suggests, a five-paragraph essay&nbsp;will contain five logical sections: introduction, three body paragraphs, and a conclusion. The introduction is always the opening paragraph in your essay and you will need to include such elements as the thesis statement and the three sub-topics which are called &lsquo;body&rsquo; paragraphs. The last paragraph is the conclusion and you will have to sum up the ideas expressed in previous paragraphs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/ozessay-five-paragraph-essay-structure-hamburger.jpg\" alt=\"Here the most basic scheme of a five paragraph essay: it\'s often likened to a hamburger and consists of an introduction, several body paragraphs and a conlcusion\" width=\"850\" height=\"473\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A good introduction has the ultimate power in either grabbing the readers&rsquo; attention or losing it. With thousands of essays out there, your reader will make a reading decision by reading the first couple of sentences and skimming through the body of the paper. Consequently, writing a good, eye-catching introduction is of ultimate importance to an effective composition.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Tips for writing an effective essay introduction</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Make a general statement and then narrow it down</em>. Generally, the way of starting an essay is the least interesting for the reader; however, it&rsquo;s a proven technique that is effective. This would be the most appropriate beginning for most academic essays that do not allow starting an essay otherwise.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Use a quote that is relevant to the topic.</em> This is generally a good and a powerful beginning for an essay that is written during high school and early college years. A quote from someone who is respected in a society will add weight to your paper and will provoke readers&rsquo; interest in the paper. However, you should bear in mind that subsequent text needs to be straight to the point and support the initial claim.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Use a rhetoric question.</em> A rhetoric question is, in essence, a disguised statement that requires no response; however, it will set your reader wondering about an issue. All you need to do is elaborate on the topic and provide convincing examples. Initial readers&rsquo; interest won&rsquo;t last long if the text that follows doesn&rsquo;t support the initial claim. Again, this type of starting your essay is not universally acceptable, and you will need to take into account the kind of essay you are working on and its purpose.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Start with an example:</em> use statistics or another example relevant to the topic. This is the opposite of the technique that&rsquo;s been mentioned first - in this case, you go from the specific to the general. Provide an example and try to establish a general pattern based on that example. Ideally, you would need several such examples to make a generalization, otherwise, you can make a false conclusion (this is called a sample, generally the more examples you have, the better the sampling, and the more accurate is the conclusion.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"Essay Structure\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/essay-structure\">How to Structure Your Essay</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"Essay Topics \" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/essay-topic\">Best Essay Topics</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"College Essay Writing \" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/college-essay/writing\">College Essay Writing</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/argumentative-essay-writing-service\">Argumentative Essay Writing Service</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/essay-structure\">Essay Structure</a>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The list of good and catchy ways of introducing your thoughts in an essay isn&rsquo;t limited to the ones mentioned above. You can you any of them or any combination thereof &ndash; anything that is interesting to the reader will work. Remember that your goal is to catch your reader&rsquo;s attention and retain it during the next several paragraphs, which will convey the main points to your reader. Once you have started with a strong introduction, it is high time to write the body paragraphs themselves.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing body paragraphs can be quite a straightforward process if one bears in mind their basic structure. Most writing experts suggest that a typical body paragraph should take the following format:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Topic sentence.</strong> This is the first sentence that introduces the main idea of the paragraph. This idea is going to be further elaborated within the same paragraph.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Details or examples supporting the idea from the topic sentence.</strong> The topic sentence should be supported with some piece of evidence that would get your essay more &lsquo;weight&rsquo; and will sound more convincing. In a case of an academic paper, you will need to mention the source of the information.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Comments/Analysis.</strong> Add two or more sentences with a commentary of the idea expressed in your main essay. If this is an essay that requires your evaluation, this can be your thoughts, ideas, impressions, judgments etc. If this is an academic essay, you will need to base your judgment on previous research to gain credibility.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Conclusion.</strong> Paragraph conclusion recaps the main paragraph idea. It also serves the purpose of connecting the previous paragraph with the next one.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Essay conclusion should be the logical finale of your writing. Once you are done writing your body paragraphs, look at the ideas expressed in the introduction and body paragraphs, you will need to restate each of them individually and then relate to the thesis statement. In this part of your essay, you will need to pay special attention to the initial requirement and see if it needs you to summarize your key elements or analyze them. Whenever you are required to do an analytical part, you are expected to dig in a bit deeper, not just merely restate the items mentioned previously.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Whatever the case, OZessay will be glad to assist you with any of the essay types, we will be happy to assist. Feel free to <a title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">contact any of our writing professionals</a>, who are always willing to provide a top quality paper that will get you a high score. Here, at <a title=\"Home Page\" href=\"https://www.OZessay.com.au\">www.OZessay.com.au</a> we are available 24/7 to help you! www.OZessay.com.au is the essay writing service you can trust.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Writing an Five-Paragraph Essay\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/writing-a-five-paragraph-essay.jpg\" alt=\"Writing an Five-Paragraph Essay\" width=\"650\" height=\"313\" /></p>','Five Paragraph Essay: Sample and Graphic Organizer from OZessay','','publish','closed','closed','','five-paragraph-essay','','','2017-05-16 14:33:40','2017-05-16 11:33:40','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(188,1,'2014-02-13 12:44:20','2014-02-13 10:44:20','','five_paragraph-essay_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','five_paragraph-essay_ozessay','','','2017-05-16 14:33:40','2017-05-16 11:33:40','',187,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/five_paragraph-essay_ozessay.jpg?v=1495534884',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(189,1,'2013-10-30 14:03:44','2013-10-30 12:03:44','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Upon entering law school, an aspiring lawyer will be required to draft cohesive, convincing law essays as part of their coursework and then as part of their subsequent career. Law essays differ from the conventional essays that undergraduate students have been required to write; consequently, know how to write these essays and knowing the differences is an advantage. The depth of analysis of the topic and level of required research is the primary difference between a legal essay and other academic papers. Background research and extensive knowledge of the topic are required in order to develop convincing legal arguments. The art of legal writing consists of the ability to write only what is necessary for as few words as possible and omitting anything that is not relevant.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>\"<em>How to write a law essay?</em>\" you may ask. No worries - we are here to help.</strong></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Context Is the King</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In traditional education, students are taught to begin outlining the main points in the first sentence of your essay, but when drafting a law essay, context is imperative. It is recommended that in a law essay, the paper begins with some legal background that provides a foundation for the arguments that will follow. Open your paper with one to three sentences of background information that provides context for the argument that follows. One example is:</p>\r\n<blockquote><em>The Supreme Court reviewed specific application of capital punishment in the 1940s and 1950s and in each reviewed case, the issue of constitutionality of the death penalty was not addressed.</em></blockquote>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Follow the Essay Format</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Essays are typically structured in a five paragraph format beginning with the introduction, following with two to three convincing paragraphs and closing with a conclusion to wrap it up.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"margin: 5px auto; display: block;\" title=\"Law Essay Structure\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/law-essay-structure.jpg\" alt=\"In introduction, you should provide background research, introduce main arguments, refer back to the question and lead in to the body of the essay. In the body, you must identify 2 or 3 main points and structure them into paragraphs, be concise, introduce primary and secondary sources and connect paragraphs to create logical flow. In the conclusion, you should sum up arguments, refer back to original question, provide closing context and remember the question. \" width=\"650\" height=\"932\" /></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">After proving the necessary background information in your introduction, it is important to directly relate the references back to the specific question being addressed. Clearly, refer to the question in the introduction portion of the essay by utilizing key terms throughout the essay to tie the arguments together. For example, if the question is: \"Does [...] bill fundamentally violate the [&hellip;] amendment?\" the essay should refer back in the following way:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>This essay will analyze the [...] bill and examine the various ways that it violates the [...] amendment.</em></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Consider the Audience</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Identify the audience of the essay prior to outlining your arguments. If your legal essay is an assignment that is meant to establish a knowledge of legal jargon and terminology learned in class, utilizing such language and terminology is appropriate. However, if the legal essay is directed towards the general public or a special interest group, legal terms are not recommended. For essays directed towards those not within the legal community, plain language is preferred and will more clearly define your arguments.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Legal essays may be written at different levels of complexity and some may require additional paragraphs for extensive arguments and supporting information. Law essays are not opinions, so writing in clear confident sentences and providing sufficient support will ensure that your essay is top notch.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you are looking for help with legal essay writing, you\'ve come to the right place. OZessay has the writers and experience to come up with a decent product that meets your needs. Email our customer support for more information or feel free to visit the order page to <a href=\"../../order\">place your order</a>.</p>','Strategies for Writing Effective Law Essays','','publish','closed','closed','','law-essay','','','2017-05-16 14:19:49','2017-05-16 11:19:49','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(190,1,'2013-10-30 14:03:44','2013-10-30 12:03:44','','law_essay-writing_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','law_essay-writing_ozessay','','','2017-05-16 14:19:49','2017-05-16 11:19:49','',189,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/law_essay-writing_ozessay.jpg?v=1495534408',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(191,1,'2013-10-30 16:18:48','2013-10-30 14:18:48','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">\"Love Is In the Air...\" may pop into your mind when you have to write a love essay on this universally present concept. Its wonderful effect on people, animals, and even plant life can be described in your love essay to give it a <strong>descriptive nature</strong>. By defining what love is all about through different perspectives can make your Love Essay a definition essay. Otherwise, you may wish to discuss different opinions of love and debate on these views, turning your love essay into an <em>argumentative or persuasive essay</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">By narrating a love story which has impressed you greatly or has inspired your feelings, the love <em>essay will take the form of a narration essay</em>. A lot of great works of literature have been inspired by the topic of love and you can enrich your love essay with some quotes and verses from these literature to add more depth to your Love Essay. While you can use any form of the&nbsp;essay to portray your views of love, it is important to keep in mind the basic rules of love essay writing and adhere to them.</p>','Love Essay: Describe Your Deepest Feelings with OZessay.com.au','','publish','closed','closed','','love-essay','','','2017-05-16 16:06:31','2017-05-16 13:06:31','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(192,1,'2013-10-30 16:18:48','2013-10-30 14:18:48','','love-essay-v3','','inherit','closed','closed','','love-essay-v3','','','2017-05-16 16:06:31','2017-05-16 13:06:31','',191,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/love-essay-v3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(193,1,'2013-10-30 14:11:47','2013-10-30 12:11:47','<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">What Is a Personal Essay?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A personal (experience) essay is a kind of an essay that gives an account of your personal experience(s). For example, &lsquo;how I spent my summer&rsquo; would be a personal essay as it tells the reader a story of <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"../../personal-experience-essay\">your experience</a></strong> during the summer period.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Function of Personal Experience Essay</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Personal essays are used predominantly to develop one&rsquo;s <strong>narrative skills</strong>. This kind of essay doesn&rsquo;t expect you to go deep into analysis &ndash; merely tell your reader what you saw, heard or lived through. Another subtype of personal essays is the one that requires you to view your experience in retrospective and analyze them. This type of essays is generally known as the <strong>reflection essay</strong>. The purpose of the reflection essay is to analyze how a certain event or a series of events impacted your life and contributed to your personal development. When you apply for university admission, you will be expected to write such a personal essay for the admission committee. The personal essay should demonstrate your dedication and commitment to the chosen field of study and where you have drawn your inspirations to pursue the chosen profession. An effective personal essay will combine both professional and personal aspects of the applicant&rsquo;s life. The crucial aspect in reflection essay writing is the introspection rather than the retrospection, i.e. you don&rsquo;t just look back and describe past events, but rather analyze those events and try to determine their impact on your personality, character etc.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">How to Format Your Personal Essay</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A personal essay in its basic form should take follows the prescribed five paragraph format, comprising the introduction, two-three body paragraphs, and the conclusion. Please read the article on <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"../../five-paragraph-essay\">essay format</a></strong> to get a better idea of how to structure your paper properly.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">How to Write Personal Essays (General Tips)</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing personal essays is generally an easy task to accomplish. Personal essays that are written retrospectively are generally easy to write.&nbsp; First of all, you are free to sound personal and use personal pronouns in your paper, so don&rsquo;t worry &ndash; the I&rsquo;s and we&rsquo;s in your paper will be absolutely ok, unlike in most other essay types. Remember that if <em>you are narrating your experiences</em>, your story needs to be lined out and logical. Avoid jumping from one event to another without making a link between the two. Try to sound natural and show your reader who you really are. Using &lsquo;fluffy&rsquo; language, being overtly witty/humorous when you are not, and especially making up events that never happened in reality are your personal essay killers. Finally, when working on your essay, make sure you proofread the paper to rid it of grammar and spelling errors. The importance of correct grammar and punctuation should never be underestimated.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Whenever you have a personal essay to work on, remember that OZessay.com.au is your reliable partner. Our professional writers know how to write personal experience essays and are always ready to provide you the assistance necessary for writing a winning essay. We guarantee you full confidentiality in the process as well as 100% authenticity on all papers we provide. Feel free to visit our <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"../../order\">order page</a></strong> or contact us at support@ozessay.com.au or via phone at (02) 8011 3512.</p>','Personal Essay: Key Stages to Writing a Paper for College Students','','publish','closed','closed','','personal-essay','','','2017-05-13 14:18:32','2017-05-13 11:18:32','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(194,1,'2013-10-30 14:11:47','2013-10-30 12:11:47','','personal_essay_writing_from_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','personal_essay_writing_from_ozessay','','','2017-05-13 14:18:32','2017-05-13 11:18:32','',193,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/personal_essay_writing_from_ozes