p style=\"text-align: left;\">A personal essay in its basic form should take follows the prescribed five paragraph format, comprising the introduction, two-three body paragraphs, and the conclusion. Please read the article on <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"../../five-paragraph-essay\">essay format</a></strong> to get a better idea of how to structure your paper properly.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">General Tips on Personal Essay Writing</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing personal essays is generally an easy task to accomplish. Personal essays that are written retrospectively are generally easy to write.&nbsp; First of all, you are free to sound personal and use personal pronouns in your paper, so don&rsquo;t worry &ndash; the I&rsquo;s and we&rsquo;s in your paper will be absolutely ok, unlike in most other essay types. Remember that if <em>you are narrating your experiences</em>, your story needs to be lined out and logical. Avoid jumping from one event to another without making a link between the two. Try to sound natural and show your reader who you really are. Using &lsquo;fluffy&rsquo; language, being overtly witty/humorous when you are not, and especially making up events that never happened, in reality, are your personal essay killers. Finally, when working on your essay, make sure you proofread the paper to rid it of grammar and spelling errors. The importance of correct grammar and punctuation should never be underestimated.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Whenever you have a personal essay to work on, remember that OZessay.com.au is your reliable partner. Our professional writers are always ready to provide you the assistance necessary for writing a winning personal essay. We guarantee you full confidentiality in the process as well as 100% authenticity on all papers we provide. Feel free to <strong><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">visit our order page</a></strong> or contact us at support@ozessay.com.au or via phone at (02) 8011 3512.</p>','Essay on Personal Experience: How to Write a Reflective Essay?','','publish','closed','closed','','personal-experience-essay','','','2017-05-24 10:44:24','2017-05-24 07:44:24','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(196,1,'2014-01-31 09:06:14','2014-01-31 07:06:14','','essay_on_personal_experience_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','essay_on_personal_experience_ozessay','','','2017-05-24 10:44:24','2017-05-24 07:44:24','',195,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/essay_on_personal_experience_ozessay.jpg?v=1495611162',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(197,1,'2013-10-30 15:02:30','2013-10-30 13:02:30','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Most people have problems when it comes to writing a Philosophy paper. They usually confuse it with a literary essay or a research paper. Others think that they are supposed to solely research and state the opinions of those scholars who hold various beliefs on a given topic. However, these are not the right approaches to consider for such a paper. You are expected to come up with a clear thesis and defend it extensively based on your individual assessment on the issue as well as other scholar\'s opinions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">First, introduce the paper with a strong and clear thesis statement that explains the problem. This is because clarity is a fundamental ingredient of a quality philosophy essay. Also, state the way in which you are going to deal with this issue.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Secondly, a few words on the structure of the philosophy essay. You should go on to the body of the essay whereby you should make your stand on the matter clear and then rationalize and support it using persuasive and substantial arguments. You should also back your view with logical explanations and relevant data. The body should also contain other people\'s opinion on the issue; both the ones that support your position and those that oppose it. You should do an in-depth analysis of their strong and weak arguments and explain how your point of view holds water as compared to those of others. You may also anticipate objections to your stand on the issue and respond to them.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">It is crucial to choose your words properly and wisely to avoid making your essay vague and misleading. You should also desist from using difficult words in an effort to impress the lecturer. Instead, look for words that are suitable and concise. This way, you will avoid passing the wrong messages and leaving the reader of your essay confused and unsure about your point of view.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">You may include quotes in your philosophy paper as well. However, always ensure that the quotes support or contradict the point that you are trying to put across. The quotes should be relevant and analyzed extensively. You should also ensure that the content of the quote has a direct link to the basis of your argument.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Lastly, you should write a solid conclusion. It should consist of your final view on the issue in question. It should reflect on the analysis you have discussed in the body of the essay. This way, the reader will be in a position to predict your opinion. Alternatively, you may choose to go against the grain and make an unexpected conclusion. Regardless of your opinion, it should have a strong connection to the position that you have been strongly advocating for on the issue. Keep in mind that the evaluator will be assessing the degree to which you have grasped the issue and how well you have argued your points. Your grade will depend on the depth and quality of the paper. Therefore, you will not achieve a standard philosophy essay through writing a sub-standard analysis.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Once you have finished writing the paper, you should proofread it to ensure that there are no grammatical errors or incomprehensible statements. You should also add examples where you feel it is necessary since philosophy thrives on definitions and examples. This is because they make the essay more persuasive. Also, check to see that the essay has a good flow and that you have communicated exactly what you wanted to say on the issue.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We have written hundreds of philosophy essays for our customers and are ready to provide assistance if you need it. Please contact our support team at <a href=\"mailto:support@ozessays.com.au\">support@ozessays.com.au</a>&nbsp;or place your order via the <a href=\"../../order\">order page</a> and we will start working on the order immediately.</p>','Philosophy Essay','','publish','closed','closed','','philosophy-essay','','','2017-05-17 11:42:49','2017-05-17 08:42:49','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(198,1,'2013-10-30 15:02:30','2013-10-30 13:02:30','','philosophy_essay-ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','philosophy_essay-ozessay','','','2017-05-17 11:42:49','2017-05-17 08:42:49','',197,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/philosophy_essay-ozessay.jpg?v=1495607699',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(199,1,'2013-10-25 12:29:38','2013-10-25 09:29:38','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a title=\"How to Write a Reflective Essay\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/reflective-essay/how-to-write\">A reflective essay</a> is a type of essay that is widely used in the academic environment.&nbsp;Since reflection essays may be complex and intellectually challenging, they are widely used by teaching institutions to boost students&rsquo; thinking and writing skills. Nevertheless, students who first come to work on such assignments often end up in a dead end, not knowing where to start or how to write a reflective essay at all. This article attempts to explain some basic notions of reflective essay writing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Reflective Essay Definition\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/reflective-essay-definition.png\" alt=\"What is a reflective essay? It\'s a type of the essay that requires you to analyza your own ideas, experiences and insights and then put them together in writing\" width=\"650\" height=\"202\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our writers guarantee the premium quality content, complete reference, and zero plagiarism.&nbsp;<a title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">Place your order here</a>&nbsp;and enjoy the result!</p>\r\n<h3>What is a Reflective Essay?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A reflective essay is a type of essay that requires you to analyze your own ideas, experiences, and insights and then put them together in writing. Essentially, writing reflective essays is all based on reflection and self-reflection: human&rsquo;s capacity to exercise introspection and willingness to explore one&rsquo;s inner thoughts and/or experiences.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><a href=\"../../reflective-essay/how-to-write\">How to Write a Reflective Essay</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../essay-structure\">Essay Structure</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../example-of-a-five-paragraph-essay\">Example of a Five Paragraph Essay</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Why is Reflective Essay Writing Important?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Reflective essay writing can be a very challenging task. The impact of such essay writing is multifaceted: starting from the obvious essay skills enhancement to the more complicated transference of self-reflection skills into real life. If taken outside the academic setting, the ability to self-reflect and find the root-cause of a given event is of great help to just about any individual.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For example, you&rsquo;ve made a mistake somewhere along the path. When you try to sit down and reflect on it, the reasons and root causes of such event become obvious to you. This, in turn, will allow you to avoid making similar mistakes in future. This is the power of analysis and self-reflection outside just the classroom setting.</p>\r\n<h3>Reflective Essay Outline Format</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">From the point of view of essay structure, any <a title=\"Reflective Essay Free Example\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/custom-essay/reflective-essay/free-example\">reflective essay</a> is still a typical essay, requiring anyone working on it to maintain the basic essay format: introduction, body paragraphs, and a conclusion.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Reflective Essay Outline Format\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/reflective_essay-outline-format.png\" alt=\"Reflective Essay Outline Format includes introduction, body and conclusion. \" width=\"650\" height=\"139\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The introduction</strong> should be the part of the essay that grabs a reader\'s attention to make them interested in the rest of the story. It should include your thesis statement and some general background information about the topic. It&rsquo;s here that you present your basic essay idea which is then elaborated in the body paragraphs. The introductory part of your essay (any essay, not just reflective one) serves the eye-catching purpose: if the reader finds your essay boring after the first couple of sentences, your paper won&rsquo;t be read any further. Academic essays, however, are different: your professors will definitely read them till the end, however, if they find them irrelevant or not to the point, your final grade will go down.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The body</strong> is the next part of the essay and provides the story itself. Body paragraphs should enumerate your main ideas and provide from three to five supporting sentences. The body is arranged to make the story flow while containing the essay\'s important points. &nbsp;The description provided in the body should be brief enough to portray the picture and long enough to make the story interesting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Ultimately, <strong>the conclusion</strong> should summarize the main ideas expressed in your paper and finalize it. It contains the lesson learned from the writer\'s reflection. The conclusion of the reflection essay should address:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Whether you achieve your aims<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;What would you like to change if you were to repeat the process<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;What were the key learning outcomes<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Will and how would you apply the gained knowledge in future work <br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;How will you propose to make improvements</p>\r\n<h3>Reflective Essay Graphic Organizer</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A graphic organizer is an essential visual aid that helps a writer accurately plan his/her essay. Most reflective essays comprise of an incident, the response and the reflection. The three parts when graphically displayed portray a clearer picture where the writer can easily see how everything fits into the big picture which is the essay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A graphic organizer is a great tool that assists a writer to get a better understanding of how to move from one part to another of her recollection. An organizer saves time since once does not have to go back to correct mistakes which will have been eradicated by the planning process.</p>\r\n<h3>Reflective Essay Writing Tips</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>TIP 1.</strong> An author should not seek to include all of his experiences in a single essay. A reflective essay should contain a single event that holds the most valuable lesson or has had the biggest impact on your life.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>TIP 2.</strong> Honesty is the best policy when it comes to writing reflective essays. The essay should not be exaggerated to the point where a reader can tell it is unreal.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>TIP 3.</strong> A reflective essay writer should ensure there are no contradicting elements in his story. Moreover, the article should be the author\'s experience and no other\'s.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>TIP 4.</strong> A student may decide to order a reflective essay from an essay writing service. The reasoning behind the above decision may be that professional writers would be a lot better at telling stories than the student which would make the essay more attractive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As such a reflection essay is usually undertaken at the graduate level, you are expected to carry out your reflections professionally, and objectively and write your reflective essay using appropriate vocabulary, and in suitable writing style.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you want to entrust the writing process to professionals, we are ready to help you&nbsp;<a title=\"Writing Help\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">write your essay effectively</a>.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Reflective Essay Writing Tips\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/reflective-essay-writing-tips.png\" alt=\"What are reflective essay writing tips? It must be a sinle event. valuable lesson, just an author\'s experience and absolutelly honest.\" width=\"650\" height=\"189\" /></p>','Reflective Essay','','publish','closed','closed','','reflective-essay','','','2017-05-23 13:40:42','2017-05-23 10:40:42','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(200,1,'2013-10-25 12:29:38','2013-10-25 09:29:38','','reflective_essay_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','reflective_essay_ozessay','','','2017-05-23 13:40:42',