ay is not a big deal&nbsp;since a persuasive essay outline is simple to follow: an introduction, body paragraphs, and a conclusion.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">10 Persuasive Essay Topics on Business</h2>\r\n<p><em>1. Innovative technology in business.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>2. The importance of human resources in a&nbsp;business environment.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>3. The ways of measuring and managing an employee retention.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>4. The effect of branding and marketing on sales of goods.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>5.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Work environment effects on productivity.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>6.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Is it possible for all businesses go green?&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>7.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Having a social network page should help promote&nbsp;business.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>8.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>A college degree does not guarantee business success.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>9.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>The main cause of business bankruptcy: poor leadership or poor management?&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>10.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Outsourcing IT departments is ineffective.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you need more persuasive essay topics here is a great list of the most popular topics of 2017.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/persuasive-writing-topics\">BEST PERSUASIVE WRITING TOPICS IN 2017</a></strong>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are given a task to write an argumentative essay on a&nbsp;business topic you may use the topics in the offered list as ideas for writing. If you are pressed for time to think over the topic, conduct research and write a well-structured essay, <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">place an order</a> for the essay on our website.&nbsp;</p>','Persuasive Writing Topics: 10 Ideas for a Successful Essay on Business','','publish','closed','closed','','10-persuasive-essay-topics-business','','','2017-05-17 13:06:34','2017-05-17 10:06:34','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(320,1,'2016-12-27 11:47:48','2016-12-27 09:47:48','','persuasive_writing_topics_on_business_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','persuasive_writing_topics_on_business_ozessay','','','2017-05-17 13:06:34','2017-05-17 10:06:34','',319,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/persuasive_writing_topics_on_business_ozessay.jpg?v=1495701712',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(321,1,'2016-12-28 16:29:18','2016-12-28 14:29:18','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/persuasive-essay-writing-service\">persuasive essay</a>&nbsp;is an essay that uses reason along with logic so the person reading it can see that one idea is more justifiable than another idea. The purpose of a persuasive essay is to influence the reader to take on a particular viewpoint or to adopt a certain action. It is imperative that the persuasive essay has solid evidence within it and sound reasoning. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-persuasive-essay\">HOW TO WRITE A PERSUASIVE ESSAY</a></strong></h4>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To write a persuasive essay is not a big deal&nbsp;since a persuasive essay outline is simple to follow: introduction, body paragraphs, and conclusion.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">10 Persuasive Essay Topics on&nbsp;Literature</h2>\r\n<p><em>1. As reflected in Beowulf, women played an important role of peacemakers in Anglo-Saxon society.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>2. Shakespeare\'s works would be more enjoyable if they were shorter. &nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>3. How to read literature like a professor: a key to effective reading.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>4. Learning language arts through literature should is a way to improve reading and writing.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>5. Norton Anthology of American literature helps students studying literature.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>6. In his novel 1984, George Orwell reveals the idea that excessive government?s control creates the&nbsp;world in which citizens are hardly alive.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>7. Hemingway portrays Santiago\'s relationship with his natural environment to show how his connection with the sea and its creatures saves the old man in the midst of his tragedy.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>8. The main idea of Romeo and Juliet is the undeniable power of love.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>9. All Quiet on the Western Front is Remark\'s fictional account of Germans\' experience in the World War I.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>10. Huxley\'s use of neologisms in Brave New World creates the atmosphere of a&nbsp;futuristic environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you need more persuasive essay topics here is a great list of the most popular topics of 2017.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/persuasive-writing-topics\">BEST PERSUASIVE WRITING TOPICS IN 2017</a></strong>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have chosen a topic from a list try to carefully think out what to write about it.&nbsp;Conduct a research and read all the available information on the topic and then start writing. If you don\'t have enough time to do this you may <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">place an order</a> and get an instant quote for an essay.&nbsp;</p>','Persuasive Writing Topics: 10 Hottest Ideas for Essays on Literature','','publish','closed','closed','','10-persuasive-essay-topics-literature','','','2017-05-12 16:28:01','2017-05-12 13:28:01','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(322,1,'2016-12-28 16:29:18','2016-12-28 14:29:18','','persuasive-essay-topics10-5-v3','','inherit','closed','closed','','persuasive-essay-topics10-5-v3','','','2017-05-12 16:28:01','2017-05-12 13:28:01','',321,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/persuasive-essay-topics10-5-v3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(323,1,'2014-02-22 15:03:07','2014-02-22 13:03:07','<h2>Tips on How to Write a Good Speech</h2>\r\n<p>Wedding, debates, ceremonies at school and other special occasions are the events you may need to prepare an effective speech for delivering there. Your speech may be either long or short, but it must be perfectly tailored to be suitable for the situation. Our writers have offered several simple tips on how to write a speech.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>1. Time</h3>\r\n<p>Understand the length of your speech. Write down the main points to cover in your speech, depending on the time you have. Divide your speech into minutes. For example, if you have 5 minutes, allocate 3 minutes of your time to the main points, and leave 2 minutes for the introduction and the conclusion, 1 minute per each.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>2. Speech Writing Outline</h3>\r\n<p>Plan and rehearse your story. Conduct research on the topic. Find the most relevant content and put it all together so that the arguments are arranged logically, in accordance with your plan. Stick to the backbone of the subject. Don&rsquo;t go beyond your topic. Use connecting words and phrases that show your thoughts to the audience.</p>\r\n<h3>3. Visual Aid</h3>\r\n<p>Prepare some visual materials (photos, documents, graphics, etc.) to demonstrate during your public speaking. It will make your speech vivid and impressive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>4. Sincerity</h3>\r\n<p>Figure out how to write a persuasive speech. Be sincere in your beliefs. You must believe in what you say to convince others. Every word in your speech should be well thought out and convey a message. If you doubt about the correct usage of the word, choose another one, simple and clear.</p>\r\n<h3>5. The Beginning and the End</h3>\r\n<p>Writing a speech conclusion and introduction is one of the toughest assignments. Here are some tips on how to write a conclusion for a speech:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Define the objective of your speech.</li>\r\n<li>Build a strong call to action. Think what you want people to do once your talk is finished.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Summarize your words in a few sentences.</li>\r\n<li>Make people show their emotions: laugh, tears, sympathy etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Some recommendations on how to write an introduction for a speech are as follows:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>It is a good practice to being your speech with writing a body first. Once you are done with the main part of your essay, write an introduction, the most important message you want to convey to your readers or audience. It must be a hook sentence - exciting and fascinating.</li>\r\n<li>Tell people about your subtopics, things you want to tell them during the speech.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ve got some simple tips on how to write a speech. Here is a short list of speech ideas that we know you will like:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Are e-books better than traditional ones?</li>\r\n<li>Does TV teach children violence?</li>\r\n<li>All people must have health insurance.</li>\r\n<li>How does artificial intelligence help e-commerce businesses?</li>\r\n<li>Why is my school the best?</li>\r\n<li>Why should I become a school captain?</li>\r\n<li>How can Facebook help you study?</li>\r\n<li>Junk food should be banned.</li>\r\n<li>Students should wear uniforms.</li>\r\n<li>All personal inventions and ideas must be patented.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>These are only examples of the topics. Larger lists are available over the Internet.</p>\r\n<h2>Types of Speech</h2>\r\n<p>There 4 main types of speech. Their names are determined by the purposes they have. See the table below:</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Type</td>\r\n<td>Purpose</td>\r\n<td>Description</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Informative</td>\r\n<td>To inform</td>\r\n<td>This type of speech delivers useful information to the audience. Usually, the speaker informs the audience about the things, objects, events, facts, etc. they don&rsquo;t know yet.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Persuasive</td>\r\n<td>To persuade</td>\r\n<td>Persuasive speech is one that is aimed to influence the audience in a way that they agree with the speaker&rsquo;s points of view and beliefs. Good examples of a persuasive speech are a debate speech or a school captain speech.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Entertaining</td>\r\n<td>To entertain</td>\r\n<td>The entertaining genre includes all kinds of excuses, after-dinner speeches, wedding speeches, etc. Typically, entertaining speech makes people cry, laugh, or show other strong feeling and emotions.Wedding soon? Here are some tips on How to write a speech for a wedding.&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Demonstrative</td>\r\n<td>To demonstrate</td>\r\n<td>Demonstrative type is a kind of &ldquo;How to&rdquo; articles which demonstrate the audience or readers &ldquo;how to do something&rdquo;. It may be different guidelines, manuals, instructions, lessons and so on.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>How Does a Speech Type Influence a Writing Style?</h2>\r\n<p>A writing style is defined as a manner of expressing your thoughts and conveying the information to the readers. The most important elements that determine one&rsquo;s writing style are as follows:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>grammar;</li>\r\n<li>punctuation;</li>\r\n<li>words choice;</li>\r\n<li>sentence/paragraph structure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>One more element your writing style depends on is a type of essay you compose. Let&rsquo;s figure out how a speech type may influence our style of writing. What are the main features of some speech types?</p>\r\n<p>Writing an inspirational speech is characterized by the following features: motivational words, real-life stories, energetic and inspirational sentences, passionate and positive conclusions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Writing a debate speech is characterized by the usage of affirmative sentences, credible information, coherent flow of thoughts, strong arguments that prove your stance.</p>\r\n<p>A speech for public speaking has the following features that make it stand out from the other types of speeches: confidence, passionate and authentic expressions, natural voice, connection with the audience, storytelling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So, as you see, each type of speech influences one&rsquo;s manner of writing. Before getting started with your story, learn how to write a speech step by step. But keep in mind that it should sound natural and clear.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Writing Template: How to Write a School Captain Speech</h2>\r\n<p>What can help you write faster? A writing template. Here is an example of a speech writing template provided by our editors.</p>\r\n<p>We hope this template will show you how to write a great persuasive speech for a school captain role.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Introduce yourself. Tell a few words why you consider you may make a good school captain.</li>\r\n<li>Write about the qualities of a great leader. Add about your personal qualities that make you stand out from the rest. Focus on your leadership qualities.</li>\r\n<li>Write about your extracurricular activities: football, basketball, music, arts, volunteer work, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Write how you could improve your school.</li>\r\n<li>Write inspiring and motivational words to other students. Think of some call to actions. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Add some creativity to your speech. Use a famous quote or a plan of your school improvements to expand your ideas.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>It is a short template that may be used as the basis for any simple speech writing for primary school, secondary school, high school, or even college. If you need an extensive speech for public speaking, you may order it from our professional writers. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>How to Write a Speech for English? Ask OZessay&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>OZessay is a top Australian essay writing platform for international students all over the world. Our writers are skilled at writing different types of essays including speech writing for English learners. By contacting us you will be also able to get tips to writing a good speech we didn&rsquo;t cover in this article.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Among our clients, there are a lot of graduates who usually ask about the tips for writing a graduation speech. There are also businessmen who need to write a speech for negotiations, workshops, presentations. So, you are welcome to contact us for any kind of writing assistance!&nbsp;</p>','How to Write a Speech','','publish','closed','closed','','how-to-write-a-speech','','','2017-09-08 12:51:43','2017-09-08 09:51:43','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(324,1,'2014-02-22 15:03:07','2014-02-22 13:03:07','','how_to_write_a_speech_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','how_to_write_a_speech_ozessay','','','2017-09-08 12:51:43','2017-09-08 09:51:43','',323,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/how_to_write_a_speech_ozessay.jpg?v=1504779338',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(325,1,'2014-04-28 15:25:41','2014-04-28 12:25:41','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The first day of college, you should have noticed the difference from high school. The people, the assignments, and your professor&rsquo;s interactions with students are more intense. So it should be no surprise that a book report is no longer standard either. These are still a requirement and will be so for your continued educational career.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Let&rsquo;s discuss how to write a book report effectively for college. If you want to save your time - <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">ask our writers to help you!</a></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">What Is a Book Report?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So far, you understand a book report to be a <strong>four or five paragraph summary of the book</strong>, proving to your teacher that you have read and understood the book. On a college level, it&rsquo;s much more complex.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"A Book Review or a Critical Review\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/critical-review.jpg\" alt=\"You must choose a position to agree or disagree with with an author and defend it. You may need to critique the text. The most important factor is to demonstrate your thorough knowledge of the text anf clearly support your position\" width=\"650\" height=\"241\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Most Typical Book Report Topics</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">When preparing your book report writing, of course, the most essential piece is discovering your book report topic. Many times your professor will indicate what topic you should write about. Other times, they will leave it up to the student.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Topics vary, including architecture, policies, performances, fashion, and other fields of literature. Don&rsquo;t allow a topic to limit you. If there\'s a listing assigned, select the one you have the greatest interest in or can learn more about. Here are 10 popular topics:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li><em>The effect of capitalism</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Building up the character</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Displacement</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Fate and free will</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Injustice</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Knowledge versus ignorance</em></li>\r\n<li><em>The complications of nationalism</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Power of wealth</em></li>\r\n<li><em>The illusion of progress</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Technology in society &ndash; good or bad</em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Identifying the Theme and Topic</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">It&rsquo;s important to know the difference between the theme and the topic. The two are highly similar. The topic is the subject of your literature. It is very specific. The theme is related to the subject but more general. It&rsquo;s what you learn from the literature.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Typical Book Report Structure</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As stated, your book report will consist of more than five paragraphs summarizing the book. There are 4 important pieces of a book report: the introduction and thesis, your opening paragraph, the body, and the conclusion. Although it&rsquo;s only four pieces listed, the body will make up the majority of your book report.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Typical Book Report Structure\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/oz-book-report.jpg\" alt=\"Typical book report consists of introduction and thesis, opening paragraph (summary), body (the book\'s analysis) and the conclusion \" width=\"650\" height=\"141\" /></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>1. Intro and Thesis<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Your introduction and a thesis are important. As with any other report, this is your opportunity to capture the reader and inform them of what you intend to discuss. Your introduction should include the title of the book, the author&rsquo;s name, and the theme of the book.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Here, you will also give your attitude toward the book. Clearly, state what the author&rsquo;s purpose was and if you are agreeing with or against his position. Include your thesis towards the end of your introductory paragraph and ensure it leads into the rest of the paper.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>2. Opening Paragraph (Summary)<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Your opening paragraph or summary should be brief. Remember, the bulk of your paper should be analytical. So you will refer to other summarizations throughout your paper as well. Your approach to the summary may vary. For instance, if your classmates have all read the book, focus your attention on something more subtle. If it&rsquo;s not well-known, you can summarize a bit more.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>3. Body (The Book&rsquo;s Analysis)<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The meat of your book report will consist of the body. This is your analysis and evaluation of the book. This needs to be as long as necessary to explain each point of your argument. The organization of these paragraphs does not need to coincide with the organization of the book. You can organize it by methods, themes, or anything else of relevance. Since this is an analytical work, you do not need to over a quote.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>4. Conclusion</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As with all other works, your conclusion will wrap up your analysis and judgment of the book. You should restate or sum up your thesis again. At this point, all your evidence should have been introduced and clearly support where you stand.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">OZessay - Your Reliable Academic Partner!</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In case you need any help with writing, please do no hesitate to <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">contact our support team for assistance</a> - our support team will help by connecting you with writers who know exactly how to write a book report. Our team of highly qualified research experts will come up with a solution that exceeds your expectations. <em><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" title=\"OzEssay is your reliable academic partner!\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/\">OZessay</a></em> is your reliable academic partner!</p>','How to Write a Book Report: A Step-by-Step Writing Instruction','','publish','closed','closed','','book-report-writing','','','2017-05-17 11:03:38','2017-05-17 08:03:38','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(326,1,'2014-04-28 15:25:41','2014-04-28 12:25:41','','how-to-write-a-book-report4-v3','','inherit','closed','closed','','how-to-write-a-book-report4-v3','','','2017-05-17 11:03:38','2017-05-17 08:03:38','',325,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/how-to-write-a-book-report4-v3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(327,1,'2014-04-28 15:57:40','2014-04-28 12:57:40','<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">10 Steps to Write a Book Report</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">It&rsquo;s important for you as a student to learn&nbsp;how to write a book report on a college level&nbsp;because you will use it beyond your graduate degree. Following the list of steps in writing a great book report we offer can help you in getting a <a title=\"How to Get Good Grades\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-get-good-grades\">high grade</a>. But we offer more than just a list of steps to take. OZessay is ready to help you in writing a winning book report. <a title=\"Ordering Procedure\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">Place</a><a title=\"Ordering Procedure\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">&nbsp;your order here</a>&nbsp;and be sure to get an A.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 1.</strong> Make sure to read the entire book. For a complete analysis, you can&rsquo;t skim through the book. Highlight important passages and take notes as you go.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 2.</strong>&nbsp;Make sure you have a clear understanding of the subject the author is conveying. You want to verify you understand his approach as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 3.</strong> Quickly review other reviews of the <a title=\"Book Authors\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/book-authors\">book</a>. This will help you narrow down interesting topics for your own paper. Search through credible sources such as scholarly sources.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 4.</strong> Determine your thesis statement. This should be summed up in one or two sentences and gives your audience a clear understanding of where you stand in your argument. Your theme needs to be specific to the author&rsquo;s theme, writing style, or about relevant characters.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 5.</strong> Gather your credible sources and specific quotes you want to use. Your professor will state in your guidelines the minimum and maximum you should include.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 6.</strong> Using your notes, assessments and reviews, outline your <a title=\"Argumentative Essay Writing Service\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/argumentative-essay-writing-service\">argument</a>, making sure it clearly supports your thesis.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 7.</strong> Now, you will outline your report. Make sure you have at least three supporting points of your thesis statement in the body of your report.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 8.</strong> Sit down and write your report based on your outline and <a title=\"Custom Research Paper\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/custom-research-paper\">research</a> materials gathered. This is considered a draft, so it does not need to be perfect at all.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 9.</strong> Edit and proof your work. If possible, have another peer review your report and offer feedback.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 10.</strong> Make sure to adequately cite your sources. To be successful in college, plagiarism should be avoided at all costs. Your professor will indicate his preferred citation method.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-literature-review\">How to Write a Literature Review</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-speech\">How to Write a Speech</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/custom-research-paper/how-to-write-a-research-paper\">Research Paper Writing</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/coursework-writing\">Coursework&nbsp;Writing</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/argumentative-essay-writing-service\">Argumentative Essay Writing Service</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you are struggling with your book report, OZessay is the company that is happy to help 24/7. We are in this business since 2006 and have the expertise required to come up with a&nbsp;text of any complexity level. Our expert writers will happily assist you with your assignment, so don\'t hesitate - <a href=\"../../order\">order a paper today</a>!</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/girl-is-working-at-the-laptop.jpg\" alt=\"Girl Is Working at the Laptop\" width=\"650\" height=\"268\" /></p>','10 Steps to a Perfect Book Report','','publish','closed','closed','','how-to-write-a-book-report','','','2017-05-16 16:20:24','2017-05-16 13:20:24','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(328,1,'2014-04-28 15:57:40','2014-04-28 12:57:40','','book-report-writing-v3','','inherit','closed','closed','','book-report-writing-v3','','','2017-05-16 16:20:24','2017-05-16 13:20:24','',327,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/book-report-writing-v3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(329,1,'2014-05-06 18:57:23','2014-05-06 15:57:23','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We&rsquo;ll bring it all into focus for you and give you an educational example of a five paragraph essay. We will begin with this clear introduction, which is exactly what your <strong>opening introduction</strong> (and first paragraph) of your essay should address. In our example of a five paragraph essay we will discuss how long we think the essay should be, the sorts of topics you could write about and how to make your essay interesting (and not too wordy).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Here is a scheme that shows the structure of a five-paragraph essay. As we can see, a&nbsp;basic five paragraph essay consists of five structural elements, which are often likened to layers of the hamburger. These structural elements include: introduction, a few body paragraphs, and a conclusion:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Five paragraph essay structure\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/ozessay-five-paragraph-essay-structure-hamburger.jpg\" alt=\"A basic five paragraph essay consists of five structural elements, which are often likened to layers of the hamburger. These structural elements include: introduction, a few body paragraphs, and a conclusion\" width=\"667\" height=\"371\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our <strong>first body paragraph</strong> (your second paragraph of your five paragraph essay) will talk about the length of your essay. Typically most lecturers or teachers will assign the length they would like your essay to be. We think it is best to draft out a word count plan first so you can break your essay down. This is extremely helpful if you feel you are procrastinating and you need a kick up the backside to get the momentum going. If you have been given the instruction that your essay should be 500 words, then the math is simple. Simple break each paragraph down into equal words and now all you have to think about is writing excellent material in 100 words per paragraph.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our <strong style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva;\">second body paragraph</strong> (your third paragraph of our example of a five paragraph essay) is what can you write about. Most lecturers will set the topic but if you want originality then you need to dig a bit deeper into the topic. What is your opinion on what you have been asked to demonstrate? Do you have a strong perspective you want to give? If so this is where you can start doing some research to prove you know your stuff. Don&rsquo;t sit on the fence when you write your essay. You are, in many cases, being asked to give your interpretation or argument to the material so bring it. If you are up for a good debate this is your opportunity to really show key strengths.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our <strong>third body paragraph</strong> (the fourth paragraph of our five paragraph essay) is to help you focus on the structure of your sentences that will create a great essay. First thing, keep your sentences short. Make a statement and then back it up. Use keywords like; in this essay, we discuss the differences, or this is how we can illustrate why this situation/event has occurred. Illustrate is a great keyword because immediately you know what you have to do and your reader is immediately influenced by this strong action word.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In our <strong>closing statement</strong> (our fifth paragraph of our example of a five paragraph essay) we want you to reflect on the points you are trying to make and reiterate them here. Remember your job in your essay is to inform and educate your reader. You want to be seen as an authority on the topic and the better research you have done the better you will write. Your research arms you with vital insights that will help you separate the facts from fiction. Your writing is then just an extension of your research.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Visit <a title=\"Order a Five Paragraph Essay at OzEssay.com.au!\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au\">www.ozessay.com.au</a> where we help you get the latest scoop on understanding essay writing. We have an example of a five-paragraph essay on just about everything and we offer useful and expert advice. Our professional researchers and writers will familiarize you with how to write an outstanding essay using some special, little-known techniques.</p>','Example of a Five-Paragraph Essay','','publish','closed','closed','','example-of-a-five-paragraph-essay','','','2017-05-16 15:16:49','2017-05-16 12:16:49','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(330,1,'2014-05-06 18:57:23','2014-05-06 15:57:23','','example_of_a_five_paragraph_essay_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','example_of_a_five_paragraph_essay_ozessay','','','2017-05-16 15:16:49','2017-05-16 12:16:49','',329,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/example_of_a_five_paragraph_essay_ozessay.jpg?v=1495719939',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(331,1,'2014-06-10 20:00:09','2014-06-10 17:00:09','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing is a skill not only valued and rewarded in higher education; it is a much-sought-after skill &ndash; craft, even &ndash; in the real world, needed for the producing of top-notch, professional emails, reports, policies, letters, articles, reviews and even advertisements.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">And though it is something taught early in one&rsquo;s education, very few people ever truly become proficient enough at writing to consider it a skill. It involves not only mastering one&rsquo;s language&nbsp;but is the product of countless hours of, well, actually writing to the point it comes as natural as speaking.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">5 TIPS on Making Your Sentences Shine</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>1. <em>Read. Read. Read.</em></strong> Then read some more. The more familiar one is with their own language (and with excellent writing), the better their own writing will be. Through reading a considerable amount (and often, as in every day and as much as possible), one is able to recognize truly excellent writing; reading, in turn, is practicing writing, because it is an exercise in grammar, vocabulary, cultural idioms, the&nbsp;nuances, and style, etc. What also aids the developing student-writer is reading beyond what is normally relevant and interesting to them. They should read everything &ndash; books in all genres, plays, short stories, blog posts, articles, reviews, the Encyclopedia, religious texts &ndash; as long as they are reading every single day, which is the most important habit for the improving student-writer.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em>2. And, well, write of course &ndash; and do it as much as humanly possible.</em></strong> Like reading on a daily basis, by writing each day the novice student-writer becomes a sculptor of words &ndash; a master of the sentence. This is, in many ways, like an athlete training for a competition. They benefit from practicing seriously for at least an hour day EVERY DAY; it becomes a healthy, fun and exciting habit, and not a chore, which then may become second nature to them, something the student-writer can look forward to each day because they are doing it well. They should write lengthy letters, long, serious, professional-type emails; they can keep a journal, start a blog, write stories &ndash; it doesn&rsquo;t matter what writing project they take on, so long as the student writes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em><strong>3. Learn the basics of your language&rsquo;s grammar and style.</strong></em> Writing is pointless without grasping the inner-workings of what constitutes appropriate grammar and style, which is a sort of code that most everyone speaking a particular language can follow, understand and read. There are several books and resources for students looking to improve the understanding of their language and how it should be read or written on paper. The Norton Field Guide to Writing: with readings and handbook helps any English speaker accomplish this goal.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em>4. Read aloud.</em></strong> It&rsquo;s true: the best writing reads how people speak. And by reading your prose aloud you notice errors, like run-on sentences, mistakes in possessive pronouns (for example, using \'they&rsquo;re\' when \'their\' should have been used), as well identifying misspellings and&nbsp;other errors in communicating an idea on paper.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em><strong>5. Get and use feedback from others.</strong></em> Quite naturally, writing is a very personal thing, but when the student-writer allows others to read their writing they are most likely receiving an objective evaluation of their writing. Readers, especially those who have much experience with reading, will identify errors in another&rsquo;s writing, either because they may have a better knowledge of grammar and syntax than the student-writer, or even because they may be more well-read than the student-writer asking them to read their work and are more equipped to recognize errors. The student-writer should beforehand also consider the skill level of this reader, to see if their comments are valid, and then determine if their comments are worth implementing into their own writing. In most cases, the reader&rsquo;s feedback will be advantageous.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Wish to know more about academic writing, practice in writing different essay types? Read the collection of </em><strong>\'HOW TO WRITE\' articles</strong><em>:&nbsp;<br /><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-persuasive-essay\">HOW TO WRITE A PERSUASIVE ESSAY</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/custom-research-paper/how-to-write-a-research-paper\">HOW TO WRITE A RESEARCH PAPER</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-book-report\">HOW TO WRITE A BOOK REPORT</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/how-to-write-a-literature-review\">HOW TO WRITE A LITERATURE REVIEW</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/reflective-essay/how-to-write\">HOW TO WRITE A REFLECTIVE ESSAY</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you do not have the time to practice or are looking for a professional service that would help you proofread your paper, check spelling, grammar and contents - OZessay is your best bet! Our professional writers will gladly assist you with improving, restructuring, and if needed - rewriting of your paper. Simply <a title=\"Click here to place your order now\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">visit our order page</a> and our writers will start work on your paper right away. We guarantee that you will enjoy the process and will want to come back to us once again. OZessay is your reliable academic partner!&nbsp;</p>','How to Develop and Enhance One\'s Writing Skills','','publish','closed','closed','','how-to-develop-and-enhance-ones-writing-skills','','','2017-05-16 16:42:43','2017-05-16 13:42:43','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(332,1,'2014-06-10 20:00:09','2014-06-10 17:00:09','','improving-writing-skills-v1','','inherit','closed','closed','','improving-writing-skills-v1','','','2017-05-16 16:42:43','2017-05-16 13:42:43','',331,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/improving-writing-skills-v1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(333,1,'2015-03-06 15:02:46','2015-03-06 13:02:46','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Just about everyone puts off completing tasks, responsibilities, and objectives at some point or another. Maybe it&rsquo;s part of our human nature, maybe it&rsquo;s because we enjoy the drama that comes with a hovering deadline or penalty. Procrastination, the action of delaying or postponing something, is part of our daily lives. Whether it&rsquo;s not writing that essay until the very last minute, paying a bill the day it&rsquo;s due rather than long before, or shopping for a holiday the day of that holiday, procrastination happens &ndash; and just about everyone is guilty of it in some way or another.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"margin: 5px auto; display: block;\" title=\"Procrastination is a Thief of Time\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/oz_procrastination.jpg\" alt=\"Procrastination is putting off the to-do list and just wasting your time\" width=\"650\" height=\"517\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">But how often do we ask ourselves WHY we procrastinate so much? It is true that life in the Western world in the 21st century is busier than ever, with constant stimulation (mostly due to technology) and a never-ending list of responsibilities that increase as time goes on. What is the reason we put off doing important things &ndash; whether in our careers, in our homes or in our daily lives? And is it a bad thing to procrastinate? At what point does it become a problem?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">People procrastinate for a number of reasons. One is a lack of resources. A task may be put off until a later date if there is a lack of money, tools, time, etc. needed to complete said task. Most times, procrastination is due to a lack of money, as things like bills, payments and financial obligations most always involve money.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">People also procrastinate because they have more important things to do, perhaps because they have bigger problems to solve. They don&rsquo;t set out to intentionally put off completing something; they do it because time is of the essence and they have other things, more important and pressing objectives, facing them. A student may put off working on a writing assignment if they need to study for an exam or prepare for an important presentation. A parent may procrastinate on fixing something in the house because they need to spend that money on feeding their children or paying the mortgage or rent. It calls for an adult decision on a pressing matter, and it often invites justified procrastination.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Other times, people procrastinate out of dread, as well. They choose not to do something because they don&rsquo;t want to do it, or because the process or perhaps the effect of doing it is not so pleasurable or something they want to do. And it&rsquo;s easier to put off doing it until it&rsquo;s absolutely necessary to do &ndash; like yard work, taxes, repairing a home and doing laundry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In conclusion, procrastination is part of life &ndash; different people for different reasons do it. Quite often, it has its perks and its drawbacks: procrastinating may be helpful for an individual&rsquo;s comfort and pleasure, but in the long-term, it can have negative consequences &ndash; such as financial penalties &ndash; and can prevent one&rsquo;s success. For example, it may be fine to procrastinate on home projects, but never a good thing to procrastinate with work-related obligations and responsibilities. So the individual must have the foresight to know what is pressing and what can be pushed aside for time being. The successful individual may be seen as a person who doesn&rsquo;t procrastinate, someone who does what they are supposed to do when they&rsquo;re supposed to do it regardless of if they want to do it or not. This is how the success guru, writer, and speaker Brian Tracy describes self-discipline as a path to success. Chuck Palahniuk, a novelist of several books including the popular Fight Club, feels people sort of like procrastinating on things in their lives. He seems to believe we need it and openly invite the drama. He says, &ldquo;People don\'t want their lives fixed. Nobody wants their problems solved. Their dramas, their distractions. Their stories resolved. Their messes cleaned up. Because what would they have left? Just the big scary unknown.&rdquo; Maybe people are programmed to procrastinate. Being attracted to conflict, people most likely &ndash; perhaps subconsciously &ndash; put off things because we are always in desperate need of a distraction from the ultimate destination: our own death.</p>','Argumentative Essay Example: Why Procrastination Is a Thief of Time?','','publish','closed','closed','','procrastination-essay','','','2017-05-13 16:18:56','2017-05-13 13:18:56','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(334,1,'2015-03-06 15:02:46','2015-03-06 13:02:46','','procrastination-essay-v2','','inherit','closed','closed','','procrastination-essay-v2','','','2017-05-13 16:18:56','2017-05-13 13:18:56','',333,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/procrastination-essay-v2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(335,1,'2015-03-06 19:36:27','2015-03-06 17:36:27','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There is a reason &ndash; or several reasons &ndash; why so much of one&rsquo;s education is spent on learning the craft of writing. It&rsquo;s not because educators are sadists who enjoy watching students toil away on tedious assignments, essays, and papers. Though the student may find writing exhausting and futile, writing assignments are actually helping them prepare for later in their adult lives, where they will have to write out of obligation, necessity or responsibility in their career and in their daily lives. People, mainly adults, write every day &ndash; emails, letters, social media posts, text messages, checks, applications. So it makes sense to embrace it, the act and skill of writing because it&rsquo;s never going away. It&rsquo;s an inevitable thing people in the Western hemisphere have to do. People will always be called on to write out their language; it&rsquo;s a form of communicated that is encouraged and appreciated by society.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"margin: 10px auto; display: block;\" title=\"Writing Skills Boost\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/writing-skills-boost.jpg\" alt=\"Writing is an important part of selfdevelopment of any personality\" width=\"650\" height=\"434\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many people find writing, the medium of communication that represents language through the inscription of signs and symbols, quite enjoyable, too. They were probably the ones inventing stories as a child to pass the time or to combat their loneliness; they were likely writing in a diary or a journal from a young age, a way to deal with their emotions, thoughts, and life experiences. They write stories or essays or articles either for money, for fun or to escape reality. Author Ray Bradbury, in Zen in the Art of Writing, said, &ldquo;You must stay drunk on writing so that reality cannot destroy you.&rdquo; Some people see writing as a puzzle they have to figure out, inserting all the right pieces at the right parts to make up something bigger than was anticipated. Some just enjoy the act of making sentences.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">And, of course, not everyone feels this way about writing. It can present a dreaded element of tedium &ndash; and it often feels like work, even to the best writers. It&rsquo;s not easy doing this: putting one word after another word to make a sentence and a complete thought. It can be like pulling teeth, and the person doing the writing something will often feel like ripping out their own hair multiples times a writing session. But the process can be worth it after something has been written &ndash; to examine, to read, something they created with their thoughts and their language. It comes down to having an expertise and at least a small bit of respect for one&rsquo;s own language. Writing is fun once the basics have been learned &ndash; the grammar and punctuation rules and standards &ndash; so the writer can be free to consider their thoughts, experiences, and even problems and put them down on paper.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing is almost as old as civilization itself. Modern anthropologists have found writings in caves that sheltered Neanderthals and historians have discovered ancient writings that were used to record information. Looking back, it&rsquo;s easy to see why even today writing is used ubiquitously in just about all cultures and societies. In many ways, writing has become a crucial way for people to communicate, to convey thoughts, needs, information and emotions to other people.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Writing, once again, is also a great outlet for creativity. Look at poems, songs, movies, articles, books, essays, letters &ndash; they all require writing. Writing something &ndash; the process of working on a project or task that requires the picking and choosing of words in one&rsquo;s language to make sentences &ndash; if looked at with the right attitude and perspective, can be a very affirming experience. But it&rsquo;s also a valuable skill to have. Since most people are required to do it, and because writing is a tedious activity most people do not enjoy, people who write very well have an advantage. People who write well probably write well because they enjoy the act of writing; more than likely, they didn&rsquo;t become an expert at the act of writing. Good writers become bloggers, authors and novelists, journalists and essayists, screenwriters and copywriters, lawyers and marketing geniuses, teachers and business people. Writing is a skill that most people need to have, of course, but one that few excel in.</p>','About Essay Writing: Example Essay from OZessay Writing Service','','publish','closed','closed','','essay-on-writing','','','2017-05-16 15:26:14','2017-05-16 12:26:14','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(336,1,'2015-03-06 19:36:27','2015-03-06 17:36:27','','essay_writing-ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','essay_writing-ozessay','','','2017-05-16 15:26:14','2017-05-16 12:26:14','',335,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/essay_writing-ozessay.jpg?v=1495545740',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(337,1,'2015-03-25 17:36:34','2015-03-25 15:36:34','<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Relationships: The Four Pillars of a Successful One</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As people continue to live life, they form relationships with other people, including <a title=\"Free Essay Sample about Family\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/essay-about-your-family\">family&nbsp;</a><a title=\"Free Essay Sample about Family\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/essay-about-your-family\">members</a> and co-workers; and also close friends who become close as if they are&nbsp;considered family.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Relationships &ndash; the way in which two or more people are connected, by&nbsp;blood, by <a title=\"Free Essay Sample about Gay Marriage\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/essay-on-gay-marriage\">marriage</a>, by work, by intimacy, by interests, or by friendship &ndash; require a lot of work, by all the people included. But relationships give meaning to life; they are a result of&nbsp;people needing each other for various reasons: for emotional support, psychological well-being, love, and affection, etc. But not all relationships are good relationships.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In good relationships, people are happy, healthy and carefree. People in successful&nbsp;relationships are peaceful and get along, encourage each other and are there for one&nbsp;another. But good relationships don&rsquo;t just happen. They are constructed &ndash; even if over time&nbsp;&ndash; by four basic pillars. They are 1) communication, 2) commonalities, 3) respect and 4)&nbsp;trust.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many students wonder how to write an essay. Here we give you a few simple tools. If, however, you do need <a title=\"Buy Essay Online\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/buy-essay\">help with essay writing</a>,&nbsp;OZessay&nbsp;is the service that is willing to assist you in any academic situation. Please feel free to contact our support team at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:support@ozessay.com.au\">support@ozessay.com.au</a>&nbsp;or place your order via&nbsp;<a href=\"../../order\">the order page</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"4 Pillars of Successful Relationships\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/pillars-for-successful-relationships.png\" alt=\"Four pillars of successful relationship are: communication, commonalities, respect and trust\" width=\"650\" height=\"235\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The first pillar holding up a good, healthy relationship is <strong>verbal communication</strong>. All relationships depend on it. Everyone has needs and concerns &ndash; and people in good relationships lessen those burdens and problems. Relationships are based on love, and when it comes down to it, love is something that is communicated among people. Information, such as one&rsquo;s needs, concerns, and frustrations, is transmitted through people, mostly through verbal communication. This includes the successful conveying or sharing of ideas, feelings, expectations, too, among people in relationships.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Relationships are based on love, and when it comes down to it, love is something that is communicated among people. Information, such as one&rsquo;s needs, concerns, and frustrations, is transmitted through people, mostly through verbal communication. This includes the successful conveying or sharing of ideas, feelings, expectations, too, among people in relationships.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The second pillar of a great relationship is the people involved having <strong>similar objectives</strong>. A family co-exists peacefully when each family member wants peace and happiness. Two young people who envision a future together both want the same thing; therefore their relationship is based on, among other things, their goal to live together throughout life on a romantic and intimate basis.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Similarities tend to bring together seemingly different people. When people can work together toward a common goal, whatever it may be, they can be looked at as essentially being part of a relationship &ndash; because they were brought together, and connected, by a common task.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Respect and trust</strong>, the last two pillars of a good relationship, go hand in hand. People have good relationships with people they respect and trust. Respect, in this case, indicates to a deep admiration for another person elicited by their abilities, qualities or achievement. Many relationships are formed out of respect, at least in non-familial situations. The same goes for trust, the firm belief in the reliability, truth, ability or strength of someone, or the absence of the truth of a statement without evidence or investigation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In conclusion, a good relationship isn&rsquo;t simply supported by just one thing, but supported by a number of things. A good relationship where two or more people are connected through something, whether blood, marriage or mutual affection, needs a steady dose of communication, similar objectives, respect, and trust &ndash; the four pillars for any successful relationship.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">When it comes to relationships among people, the key is maximizing those moments of selflessness and putting the focus on that other person or group of people. This especially pertains to ones with family members and spouses &ndash; or would-be spouses. But these relationships would also crumble to the ground without the other three pillars &ndash; without trust and respect and commonalities shared and practiced among the people comprising these relationships.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Once again, relationships require constant work and focus and patience &ndash; but it&rsquo;s supposed to be worth it: successful, happy and healthy relationships equate to a high quality of life. Research indicates that people need other people in order to live long, happy and healthy lives, which requires happy and healthy relationships among people. It&rsquo;s a simple notion, really. But it works &ndash; and has always worked.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you have&nbsp;a writing assignment&nbsp;to work on, OZessay will be happy&nbsp;<a title=\"Writing Help\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">to assist</a>. We guarantee that your essay, research paper or dissertation on tourism will be written at a&nbsp;top-notch level, delivered to you within the deadline and 100% authentic. OZessay is the service you can trust!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Happy Couple Watches the City Lights\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/happy-couple.jpg\" alt=\"Happy Couple Watches the City Lights\" width=\"650\" height=\"283\" /></p>','Relationships: The Four Pillars of a Successful One','','publish','closed','closed','','essay-about-relationships-four-pillars-of-a-successful-relationship','','','2017-05-17 12:21:23','2017-05-17 09:21:23','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(338,1,'2015-03-25 17:36:34','2015-03-25 15:36:34','','relationships4-v2','','inherit','closed','closed','','relationships4-v2','','','2017-05-17 12:21:23','2017-05-17 09:21:23','',337,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/relationships4-v2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(339,1,'2017-02-20 11:47:11','2017-02-20 09:47:11','<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Communication Strategies</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Whether we know it or not, communication is a part of our lives. From nonverbal cues to subtle changes in inflections, it\'s a wide-ranging topic that leaves an imprint on everything we do. Looking at what communication is and how it impacts the world around us only improves our perspectives.</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">The Role Of Communication In Our Lives</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Every connection relies on the simple act of communication. No matter where you are or who you encounter, this function is inevitable. That shop you visit every week, the cab driver that takes you to the airport and the worker you interact with on a daily basis, it all matters.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Think about how you address everyone in your life. Do you speak differently to strangers than you do to the loved ones? Are you cautious about what you write on public comments of a website? These are just some of the areas you face when dealing with the daily challenges of communication. While it may not seem obvious, communication strategy is just another important part of this subject</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Communication and Communication Strategies</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">What is communication? The term communication is often defined as information that creates a connection between people. That extensive definition is as broad ranging as the subject itself. For this reason, it\'s easier to explore the subject by its three distinctive types.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Verbal Communication Strategies</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Verbal communication covers all of the words and speech patterns we use. It\'s often considered the easiest way to relate information to other people. An example of this usage relates to a standard business meeting.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Nonverbal Communication Strategies</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Nonverbal communication is an all-encompassing aspect of how we present details to be other people. In many circles, it is also called \"body language.\" Every movement we make&nbsp;both consciously and unconsciously fits into this category. One of the best examples of its use is in a romantic relationship. Subtle body cues such as a person crossing their arms may mean a lack of interest during a date. An opposite reaction would be found in a person leaning forward.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Written Communication Strategies</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Written information comes in every sector. From texts to books, anything that is written falls into this category. The Internet\'s rise in popularity is the leading example of how this type of communication is essential to today\'s society. Just navigating a search engine or blog requires an exclusive database of words and symbols.</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">What Spheres Can People Apply Communication Strategies In?</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">The act of communication can be applied to every part of our lives. It\'s not just for our personal relationships, the simple act of communicating with another person can increase business opportunities. Among common components of communication strategy, the sphere that seems the benefit the most from careful planning is the workplace. Whether reaching out to a boss or giving instructions to a new employee, this area relies on steady, constant and easy to understand forms of communication.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Among spheres, personal relationships can also be divided into sections that see benefits from coaching and mentoring. A communication strategy writing service usually includes all of these elements. They provide valuable tools that address more than just communication strategies to stakeholders.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/strategies-for-communication.jpg\" alt=\"Communication\" width=\"750\" height=\"363\" /></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Communication Strategies In Different Cultures</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Every culture views communication differently. Words that you might say to someone in one culture might be viewed as an insult in another. Understanding those subtle differences is key to creating a social or professional bond.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Businesses throughout the world are encouraging global commerce. This push towards having employees and connections throughout the world highlight the importance of communication strategies in the workplace. Having insights into the world\'s cultural differences can lead to better deals that help you as well as your company finds success.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">In terms of personal connections, communications can be even more difficult to navigate. Relationships grow and change based on how we communicate with one another. Adding cultural differences makes it tricky, but easy to work with if you have the right counseling. Sign up now for help with this complicated category.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>If you are to write an essay on business here is a list of good persuasive essay topics on business communication:</em></p>\r\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a title=\"Persuasive Essay Topics on Business\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/10-persuasive-essay-topics-business-communication\">10 PERSUASIVE ESSAY TOPICS: BUSINESS COMMUNICATION</a></strong></h4>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">How Communication Strategies Influence The Effectiveness Of Communication</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">A good strategy can help anyone meet their goals. Communication strategies are tailored to produce optimum results that highlight one or more categories. Not all options are created alike, so it\'s vital to choose a plan that accurately reflects the situation. Effective communication strategies are the key to successfully navigating both personal and professional relationships.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Coaching and mentoring can help anyone tackle their strengths and weaknesses when it comes to the subject. American communication strategy writing helps make the difference when developing crucial communicative strategies.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><a title=\"Order Page\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">Order</a> a communications strategies paper online and watch it improve the way you connect with the world.</p>','Effective Communication Strategies','','publish','closed','closed','','effective-communication-strategies','','','2017-05-13 14:15:52','2017-05-13 11:15:52','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(340,1,'2017-02-20 11:47:11','2017-02-20 09:47:11','','communication-strategies-v1','','inherit','closed','closed','','communication-strategies-v1','','','2017-05-13 14:15:52','2017-05-13 11:15:52','',339,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/communication-strategies-v1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(341,1,'2015-04-03 19:23:20','2015-04-03 16:23:20','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The college years are a wonderful time in a one&rsquo;s life where they toe the line of adulthood but find themselves exempt from most of its responsibilities. No, college is not for everyone, but those who do get the privilege of attending a university or college, a school of higher education, find themselves getting to take a break before real life sets in. Other 20-somethings are working 40-hour jobs, raising families, paying bills and mortgages. College undergraduate students &ndash; a majority of who are 18 to 22 years old, or maybe a little older for graduate students &ndash; get to attend classes, hear lectures, sleep in and stay up late. But they also get to learn things &ndash; fun things, things that matter, things that will help them for the rest of their life.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">After graduating from high school, many people have a very important decision to make: is it best to jump headfirst into the work force and get a job right away? Or would it be smarter to think ahead and get a strong foundation of education, such as a bachelor&rsquo;s degree? Statistics indicate that people with a college degree tend to have more earning power over someone without one, which means they will make more money and may also have a higher quality of life during their lifetime. Education goes a long way. To many, it&rsquo;s part of an essential recipe for success. There are many sayings about success and what it takes, why it matters, how it&rsquo;s accomplished, how it is sustained over a long period of time. There is one school of thought that says a person&rsquo;s level of success matches their ability to have foresight. In other words, when a person can look ahead, long into the future, to make current decisions that affect their future, they are likely to be successful. The same is true with the opposite, as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many factors decide if one attends college: such as finances, aspirations, talents, intelligence, and character, to name only a few. In some families, a person is expected to attend college after graduating from high school. It is not only a tradition in their household but a rite of passage. Attending college and graduating with a degree, for some, is something they are expected to do because having an education will not only benefit them their entire life, it is also a valuable experience during which they learn a lot about themselves, about the world around them, and about life. In college, students are taught important bits of knowledge that help them to better understand the world, to better understand people &ndash; including themselves &ndash; and they learn important skills that are valuable and needed in the real world. They are taught critical-thinking skills, communication and interpersonal skills, research and language skills. And since the point of education is to become self-educated, students in college are trained to be resourceful and successful in the real world. This means they are taught, over and over and over again, to find the answers to things they do not know; and they&rsquo;re taught how tofind solutions to problems.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The college years are a very exciting time in one&rsquo;s life. It&rsquo;s when a person has their entire future in front of them &ndash; and it&rsquo;s a future that looks very appealing and pleasant. Yes, it&rsquo;s a time of fun, of celebration and excitement. But it&rsquo;s also a time for working hard, studying, preparing and discovering what it is one wants to become in life, in their career, and in their personal lives. The work incollege is not easy but quite demanding and hard. There is a ton of reading for long hours, conducting tedious research, and students in college spend a lot of time writing &ndash; which, let&rsquo;s face it, is not everyone&rsquo;s favorite activity. Nonetheless, it&rsquo;s more thanworth it: spending four or so years learning and better one&rsquo;s self to make one&rsquo;s life better and more fulfilling. It seems like a no-brainer.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/essay-about-college.jpg\" alt=\"Essay about College\" width=\"650\" height=\"308\" /></p>','Essay About College','','publish','closed','closed','','a-story-of-college-life','','','2017-05-17 12:58:31','2017-05-17 09:58:31','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(342,1,'2015-04-03 19:23:20','2015-04-03 16:23:20','','college_essay_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','college_essay_ozessay',''