f inspiration.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">No time to focus on writing your own persuasive&nbsp;essay? We can write one for you! Feel free to order a custom-written persuasive&nbsp;essay&nbsp;at very reasonable rates. Ordering is easy! Just tell us the instructions, no immediate payment is necessary. When we are ready to start writing, we will let you know.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/persuasive-essay-examples\">PERSUASIVE ESSAY EXAMPLES</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">But first, how can you ensure that a topic is a good one to write about? After all, the quality of persuasive writing is often a product of the topic itself. If your chosen topic doesn\'t have a compelling argument to it, you won\'t be able to produce a compelling argument in your paper, no matter how well you write.</p>\r\n<p>Here is a guide to deciphering the quality of persuasive writing topics, so that you\'ll always come up with a high-quality persuasive argument.</p>\r\n<h2>A Strong Persuasive Essay Topic Has Two Strong Sides</h2>\r\n<p>In the writing (and arguing) fields, there\'s a name for propping up a weak defense to oppose, making your job easier. It\'s called <strong>a strawman argument</strong>, and it weakens the overall quality of your essay.</p>\r\n<blockquote>For example, no one wants to read a paper in which you state \"vegetables are healthy\". This is a generally well-known fact, and any counter argument you could defend against would be a strawman.</blockquote>\r\n<p>You want to pick only persuasive essay topics that have two strong sides from which to choose. These are usually issues that aren\'t agreed upon, even in modern society. Some examples would be:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>Capitalism only protects the interests of the rich</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Standardized tests are good judge of intellect</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>These are issues that are often debated&nbsp;because the arguments surrounding them are compelling.</p>\r\n<h2>Most Good Persuasive Topics Take Research to Support Your Side</h2>\r\n<p>There are some exceptions to this, namely when the topic is purely philosophical, and the essay involves a simple opinionated statement and support, but most persuasive topics take some research and evidence to support your statement of opinion.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Here are some examples:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">1. If your topic statement is \'<em>The Modern Education System Is Failing Students\'</em>, you wouldn\'t just want to state why you think this is true. The best way to persuade is to compile evidence. Stats about how grades are dropping nationwide, or how high school grads are increasingly unprepared for higher education would be better evidence than your opinion.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">2. Historical persuasive essay writing topics follow the same rules. If you\'re, for example, arguing that the <em>United States was never really \"the land of opportunity\"</em>, you could argue that minorities in early American history weren\'t given their fair chance at success, rather than simply saying it\'s true because that\'s the&nbsp;way you feel.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/persuasive-essay-writing-service\">PERSUASIVE ESSAY WRITING SERVICE</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Even when picking from a list of good persuasive writing topics for a school assignment, undoubtedly some will be stronger than others, and as a result, some will give your writing more potential.</p>\r\n<p>So how can you recognize some really compelling persuasive writing essay topics? A topic with a lot of argument surrounding it is better than one that\'s generally agreed upon, and a topic that necessitates research and statistics as evidence is generally more effective than a simple opinion statement.</p>\r\n<p>Now that you know the recipe for success, you can get started generating your own great topics for persuasive writing!</p>','Persuasive Writing Topics','','publish','closed','closed','','persuasive-writing-topics','','','2017-08-10 14:46:30','2017-08-10 11:46:30','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(460,1,'2016-11-19 08:39:29','2016-11-19 06:39:29','','150-topics-for-your-persuasive-essay-v4','','inherit','closed','closed','','150-topics-for-your-persuasive-essay-v4','','','2017-08-10 14:46:30','2017-08-10 11:46:30','',459,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/150-topics-for-your-persuasive-essay-v4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(461,1,'2016-08-29 10:30:22','2016-08-29 07:30:22','<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">What Is an Expository Essay</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/expository-essay\">expository essay</a> is a type of essay writing that involves substantiating the idea with facts, and presenting a written argument that is clear and compelling. As you see, the expository essay definition is simple, therefore, to write an essay of such a type is not a problem for students. But! To choose the best topic&nbsp;out of top expository essay topics can become a real challenge for many students. That\'s why we chose the most popular and interesting topics to make this process as easy as possible for you.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/free-expository-essay-topics\">20 FREE EXPOSITORY ESSAY TOPICS</a></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you are looking for expository essay examples you can read a great one below.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">5 Tips to Become a Never-Give-Up Person</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">All too often in life people end up stopping before they even succeed in meeting their goals. Whatever the reason might be, there is a way to get where you want to be in no time at all. It all starts by having the will and the attitude to never give up and keep on fighting. To help you along the way, there are a few simple things that you can do.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin: 5px auto 5px auto;\" title=\"Never-Give-Up-Person\" src=\"https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articles/never-give-up-guy.jpg\" alt=\"Never give up person\" width=\"650\" height=\"541\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">TIP 1. Push forward</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The first step to reaching your goals is to stay alive. So long as you are still alive, you stand a chance at being able to do anything you want. No one can stop you from striving to do all of the things you want to do in life when you are alive and able to move about. The only time someone should be able to stop you from becoming the person you want to be is if you are no longer here. Don\'t allow someone to talk you out of your dreams and aspirations. Take control and keep pushing forward to get where you want to be in life. It is only a matter of time.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">TIP 2. Set your expectations a little lower</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Oftentimes, people set their expectations so high that there is no way they can ever meet them. Most people who are successful aren\'t successful overnight. It takes a lot of time and patience to get where you want to be. Most of the stories that you hear about someone making it big overnight are the result of good marketing tactics and nothing more. While some of the stories could be true, there is often more to it than what you are being told.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Don\'t try to guess how someone became successful. Focus on doing what you need to in order to achieve your dreams and goals. Very few people will achieve success so quickly. If you expect to turn into an overnight sensation, you are going to wind up disappointing yourself and feeling even more depressed when things don\'t turn out that way. Instead of setting yourself up for failure, consider giving yourself goals that you can achieve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">TIP 3. You are stronger than you give yourself credit for</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Oftentimes, people find themselves struggling to handle things. They think the pressure is just too much for them to bear. Don\'t give in to the pressure. If you keep doing the same things and not getting results, you can expect that you are going to keep failing. You have to experiment with different things and angles. As long as you keep trying different things, you are bound to end up succeeding at some point in time along the way. Keep persevering and you will eventually find what works.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">TIP 4. Fake it a little</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">At some point in time or another, just about everyone has faked how successful they are. There is no reason why you can\'t do the same thing. You don\'t need to go out there and start lying about what you have achieved, but that you can act like you are already successful. When you act successful, it changes the way you view the world as a whole. It helps you to strive to be more successful and achieve the things you want in life. Having the right mindset can go a long way in becoming the entrepreneur you want to be.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">TIP 5. Stop comparing yourself to someone who is already successful</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Just because you know someone who is doing amazing, that doesn\'t mean that you know the specifics behind their story. You don\'t know what it is really like for them. Even when you think you know everything, you don\'t. Allowing yourself to get sucked into the whole mess will only end up causing you to struggle. When you are at your lowest, you end up taking a lot of risks because you figure you have nothing to lose. It is at that point that you are probably going to end up taking your biggest leap of faith and end up succeeding.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This small dip often comes right before you are successful and hit it big. If you never hit your low point, how can you possibly appreciate the high points that are coming your way? No one just walks into an overnight success. You have to continue taking risks and striving to reach your goal. Otherwise, you will never get where you want to be in life.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">By following the tips above, you can be successful. It is all a matter of saying to yourself, \"I will never give up.\" When you are able to get into the right mindset, you can truly achieve anything you want in life. Don\'t beat yourself up if it doesn\'t happen overnight. With enough time, patience and a willingness to keep on persevering, you will get where you want to be in no time at all. You are in complete control of your destiny. Make it a good one.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<style type=\"text/css\"><!--\r\n<g class=\"gr_ gr_112 gr-alert gr_spell gr_disable_anim_appear ContextualSpelling ins-del multiReplace\" id=\"112\" data-gr-id=\"112\">td</g> {border: 1px solid #ccc;}br {mso-data-<a href=\"placement:same-cell;}--\">placement:same-cell;}--</a>>\r\n--></style>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you need any assistance with your essay writing you can contact our friendly support team and we will gladly help you or you can&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">place an order</a>&nbsp;and our professionals will write a great paper for you.</p>','Expository Essay Example: 5 Tips to Become a Never-Give-Up Person','','publish','closed','closed','','custom-essay/expository-essay/free-example','','','2017-05-13 14:42:08','2017-05-13 11:42:08','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(462,1,'2016-08-29 10:30:22','2016-08-29 07:30:22','','expository-essay-example4-v3','','inherit','closed','closed','','expository-essay-example4-v3','','','2017-05-13 14:42:08','2017-05-13 11:42:08','',461,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/content/3/en/images/articl