,(490,1,'2017-06-01 16:05:43','2017-06-01 13:05:43','','ozessay_review_1','','inherit','closed','closed','','ozessay_review_1','','','2017-06-01 16:47:32','2017-06-01 13:47:32','',489,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/ozessay_review_1.jpg?v=1496323399',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(491,1,'2017-07-10 15:02:08','2017-07-10 12:02:08','<p dir=\"ltr\">Narrative writing is defined as any kind of writing that tells a story.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Narrative writing is usually understood as a fiction story that tells us about imaginary events and characters. But narrative writing can be easily referred to non-fiction, that latter being a story based on real facts. In the case when we consider narrative writing to be non-fiction it should be a true story, a biography.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Each type of academic writing has its purpose. Students learn to express their thoughts and ideas in a logical manner. What is the purpose of narrative writing? The main aim is to master the art of storytelling. Writing a narrative essay you understand better your feeling and emotions experienced, entertain your readers and learn how to write an essay.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A lot of people confuse narrative and descriptive. Let&rsquo;s see the difference between descriptive and narrative writing. Unlike a narrative essay which is personal experience story, a descriptive essay is about some particular place, event or person. It doesn&rsquo;t tell any story.</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Tell Your Personal Story</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Follow the rules for narrative writing. OZessay writers have prepared a short information on writing an essay. Read it carefully to get your narrative writing stimulus.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Need to tell your story? Here are key features of narrative writing:</p>\r\n<p><strong>1.</strong> Avoid using complex words. Your story should be clear for the reader.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2.</strong> There&rsquo;s no necessity to describe every of your steps and movements.</p>\r\n<p><strong>3.</strong> Write only about your own experience.</p>\r\n<p><strong>4.</strong> Let your story be dynamic. Use the same words and phrases as you would use in your speech when telling the same story.</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.</strong> Don&rsquo;t use too many references. If it\'s possible to cite a helpful source, do it in a list of references.</p>\r\n<p><strong>6.</strong> Don&rsquo;t forget about the narrative writing prompts. Ask yourself what you would like to write about. Your response will give you a topic.</p>\r\n<p><strong>7.</strong> One more important thing to bear in mind when writing is to include 5 elements of narrative writing into your story:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">A plot is a whole story from the beginning to the end, it is what happens with the characters. Conflict is usually referred to the plot and is a kind of fight between the forces.</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">A setting is a time and area the story takes place in.</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">Characters are divided into two types and called protagonists and antagonists. Typically, a protagonist is the main and positive hero. An antagonist is opposed to a protagonist and is considered to be negative or quite different from the protagonist.</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">A theme is a central idea around which everything happens.</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">A point of view is a final opinion that can be told by the 1st person narrator or the 3rd person narrator.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>8. Techniques of narrative writing known also as literary devices will make all types of narrative writing more interesting and exciting. They include imagery, alliteration, hyperbole, symbolism, humor etc.</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Outline Your Text</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As any other types of essays, a narrative essay has its structure. Narrative writing structure is as follows:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">First is an orientation that tells the readers what the story will be about, introduces the characters and the scene of the events.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Then goes the main body of the story which includes the complication and climax. The development of complication sets the sequence of exciting events and the climax is a peak of rising actions.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The final part of narrative writing is a resolution which means the aftermath of the story.</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Let Your Story Be Interesting</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you are looking for some narrative writing topics here are some personal narrative writing ideas you may use to create your topic:</p>\r\n<p>- Sometimes life gives choices. Write if you had a time when your choice was too difficult and how you got over it.</p>\r\n<p>- Fears are a part of growing up. Write about your greatest fear ever and how you have overcome it.</p>\r\n<p>- Changes in life are inevitable. Write about a period of your life when you changed greatly.</p>\r\n<p>- Write about the largest risk you have ever taken.</p>\r\n<p>- Write a time in your life when you were stressed out and how you have combatted the stress.</p>\r\n<p>- Write about your favorite teacher and how he/she inspired you.</p>\r\n<p>- Write about a time when you understood that social media influenced you.</p>\r\n<p>- Write about your everyday problems that bother you. Are there any solutions?</p>\r\n<p>- Write about a period of your life when you started living on your own.</p>\r\n<p>- Write about the things you would like to change in your life.</p>\r\n<p>Let this article be a narrative writing stimulus for you. If you need some narrative writing examples, our professional writers are ready to provide the best samples for you.</p>','Narrative Writing','','publish','closed','closed','','narrative-writing','','','2017-07-19 16:02:16','2017-07-19 13:02:16','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(492,1,'2017-07-10 15:02:08','2017-07-10 12:02:08','','narrative_writing_ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','narrative_writing_ozessay','','','2017-07-19 16:02:16','2017-07-19 13:02:16','',491,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/narrative_writing_ozessay.jpg?v=1499776354',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(493,1,'2017-07-10 15:05:23','2017-07-10 12:05:23','<h2>Narrative Essay: to tell or to teach?</h2>\r\n<p>Almost every college student knows what a narrative essay is all about. And if you ask them to define a narrative essay they will answer that a narrative essay is an essay which tells a story from person\'s life and gives lessons to its readers. But only 2 out of 10 students know how to write a narrative worth reading. Today is your day if you came across this article, cause in this article, we will tell you a few secrets of writing a winning narrative essay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>How to Write a Good Narrative in 6 Steps</h2>\r\n<p>Narrative style writing quite differs from other writing styles. Composing such an essay you present your experience, while readers draw their own conclusions. So, you do not have to sum things up for your readers, but rather let them do it on their own. Good narrative writing requires you to follow 6 steps to get a perfect product</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1.</strong> Start with a catchy phrase</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2.</strong> Set the scene</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3.</strong> Determine the goal</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4.</strong> Use truthful details</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5.</strong> Write sequentially</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 6.</strong> Restate your goal</p>\r\n<p>Good narrative writing also requires you to include interesting facts and events written in an appealing way. Using dialogue in narrative writing is one, but not the only trick to creating a stick-out essay. Here are a few more useful tips for you to write a good narrative:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Use various grammar constructions</li>\r\n<li>Use anecdotes in your essay</li>\r\n<li>Use different connective words: <em>thus</em>, <em>however</em>, or <em>for instance</em></li>\r\n<li>Try your phrases and words to be lively and emotional</li>\r\n<li>And finally, try to record yourself while composing the story for your story flow to be organized</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Writing Narrative Prompts</h2>\r\n<p>Now you know 6 basic steps and some tips that will definitely help you create a great essay, but there are 3 more things you should take into account while writing.</p>\r\n<p>1. Stick to the first-person narrative, since the writer is the one who experienced the events described in the essay.</p>\r\n<p>2. Tend to purity. Try to avoid complex sentences and syntax. Clearly distribute main ideas throughout the text.</p>\r\n<p>3. Use dynamic words to keep your reader interested. It\'s also a good idea to use idioms and turns of phrase you usually use in your everyday speech. Adhere to active constructions, not passive ones.</p>\r\n<h2>Narrative Writing Structure</h2>\r\n<p>How to write narrative essay step by step? Narrative writing guideline tells us that for our essay to get the highest grade we should strictly adhere to a standard essay format: an introduction, body paragraphs, and a conclusion.</p>\r\n<p>How to write a good narrative introduction then?</p>\r\n<p>The <em>introductory</em>, or opening, paragraph should reveal the essence of what you are going to describe as well as your point of view.</p>\r\n<p>The <em>body paragraphs</em> tell the readers about the event itself that took place in the past and happened to you and describes your, author&rsquo;s, reaction and feeling about that. There are two possible ways to write the story facts, and both of them are correct. The first way is to describe them sequentially or you can group them by the importance level. It&rsquo;s up to you to decide which way to choose.</p>\r\n<p>The c<em>oncluding paragraph</em> wraps up and states the point of the story, whether it is a lesson or a learning experience.</p>\r\n<p>If you are searching for the requests as follows:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>how to write a narrative letter</em></li>\r\n<li><em>how to write a narrative essay</em></li>\r\n<li><em>how to write a short narrative story</em></li>\r\n<li><em>template for narrative writing</em></li>\r\n<li><em>how to write </em>a narrative examples</li>\r\n<li><em>how to write a narrative for kids</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>you are always welcome at OZessay - a professional help from experts. <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">Place an order</a> and stop worrying about your grades! Moreover, at OZessay you can also get an up-to-date list of narrative writing topics of 2017 that will definitely help you compose your own one.&nbsp;</p>','How to Write a Narrative?','','publish','closed','closed','','how-to-write-a-narrative','','','2017-08-10 14:52:07','2017-08-10 11:52:07','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(494,1,'2017-07-10 15:05:23','2017-07-10 12:05:23','','how-to-write-a-narrative-ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','how-to-write-a-narrative-ozessay','','','2017-08-10 14:52:07','2017-08-10 11:52:07','',493,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/how-to-write-a-narrative-ozessay.jpg?v=1502365936',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(495,1,'2017-07-14 11:49:45','2017-07-14 08:49:45','<p>A <strong>research report sample</strong> is a completed written assignment, namely, a research report that serves to help students compose their own one. Research report examples can be of various areas and fields of study:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>psychology research reports sample</li>\r\n<li>education research report sample</li>\r\n<li>business research report sample</li>\r\n<li>marketing research analysis report sample</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Students can be assigned to write a research paper, and therefore a research report, on any topic possible. For example, research<em> report on women empowerment</em> or <em>research report on online shopping</em>, as well as <em>research report psychology issues</em>. Whatever the subject may be, the best way for students to write a good report is to look through research reports examples and examine them, i.e. to pay attention to report structure, format and strictly adhere to them while writing their own report.</p>\r\n<p>Sometimes students confuse the notion of a research report and of a research proposal. Not to be mistaken again let&rsquo;s clear up the main difference between them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A <em><strong>research proposal</strong></em> is the beginning of the research paper, whereas a <em><strong>research report</strong></em> is its culmination. So there is a significant difference between a research report proposal example (or also research proposal report example) and a research report example.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To find a good example of a qualitative research report is not as easy as it first seems.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A proven way to get a sample paper of high quality is to get it from professional writers. OZessay, a premium assignment writing service, has a team of real experts, qualified in the definite field of study each. They&rsquo;ve written thousands of academic papers on a wide range of topics and of different complexity levels. Some sample papers of theirs you can find on our website. The top samples are as follows:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Article critique</li>\r\n<li>Assessment</li>\r\n<li>Case study</li>\r\n<li>Dissertation chapter</li>\r\n<li>Dissertation proposal</li>\r\n<li>Essay</li>\r\n<li>Literature review</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you are looking for a good example of a qualitative research report, e.g. sample business research report or research report example psychology topics, our expert writers are always ready to assist you and meet your requirements.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Since research report examples for students are very helpful, be it research report example mla style or apa research report example, we offer you to <a href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">order a great paper</a> from us and always have it before you eyes.</p>','Research Report Example','','publish','closed','closed','','research-report-example','','','2017-07-14 12:10:14','2017-07-14 09:10:14','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(496,1,'2017-07-14 11:49:45','2017-07-14 08:49:45','','research-report-example','','inherit','closed','closed','','research-report-example','','','2017-07-14 12:10:14','2017-07-14 09:10:14','',495,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/research-report-example.jpg?v=1500023295',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(497,1,'2017-07-14 15:55:17','2017-07-14 12:55:17','<blockquote>\r\n<p>Learn how to write a research report in just 4 minutes with an ultimate guide from OZessay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>A research report is a result of a scientific investigation, a brief explanation of the research conducted.</strong> A research report is used to tell your instructor or fellow scientists about the process of investigation, your findings and the importance of your research work. If you need to write a high school research report or a college one, you may find useful the following information.</p>\r\n<p>To write a clear research report students should adhere to the guidelines of academic writing. Proper research report structure ensures that the information is interpreted in the right manner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Parts of Research Report | Step by Step Guide on How to Write a Report on a Research Paper</h2>\r\n<p>How to write a report on research? Let&rsquo;s take a closer look at what each part of research report contains.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>The body is the most important part of research report structure that consists of 4 main sections:&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Introduction</li>\r\n<li>Findings</li>\r\n<li>Conclusions</li>\r\n<li>Recommendations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>When you think of research report steps, the first one you should start your writing with is the body. Write these 4 parts first before the rest of the paper.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here is a table containing all parts of a research report and a brief description to each of them:</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 505px; width: 762px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>#</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\"><strong>Research Report Sections/ Parts</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\"><strong>What Is Written in Research Report Section</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>1</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Title Page</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">It contains a title, the name of the author, submission date.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>2</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px; text-align: left;\">Contents</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">They&nbsp;contain&nbsp;a list of sections, subsections, etc.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>3</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Executive Summary or Abstract</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">It is an overview of the research. Usually, it consists of two to four paragraphs in length. An abstract is a kind of hook that aims to capture your reader&rsquo;s attention.&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>4</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Introduction of Research Report</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">The Introduction contains the information on the key question of a research report and is divided into 4 components: Purpose, Background, Methods of Investigation, Scope. Usually, it is written in present or past tenses with format-numbered headings. Let&rsquo;s figure out what to write in each of these components of a research report.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>4.1</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Purpose</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">It specifies the objectives of a given report. This part includes also the information on what a research report recommends.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>4.2</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Background</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">It describes the situation or issue which caused the investigation. This part refers to secondary resources, for example, newspaper reports. In other words, it may refer to the findings obtained by other researchers.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>4.3</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">The Method of Investigation or Methodology of Research Report</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">It tells about the ways the research was conducted and is usually called primary data as it is discovered by the author of the paper.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>4.4</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Scope</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">The Scope describes all the areas of research conducted. It may include reasons and consequences.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>5</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Findings and Results</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">They are aimed to summarize, analyze and comment the facts and information obtained during the research. You shouldn&rsquo;t include too much information not to bury the most important results. Don&rsquo;t try to interpret or evaluate the facts and better provide a link to the conclusion section to discuss your findings there.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>6</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Research Report Conclusion</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">The Conclusion contains deductions based on your findings, and logically leads to the last body section of the research report called Recommendations.&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29px; text-align: center;\"><strong>7</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29px;\">Recommendations</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29px;\">They are the assumptions and suggestions based on the research report conclusions. This part shows how the findings might be applied.&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 29.0938px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 45px; height: 29.0938px; text-align: center;\"><strong>8</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 29.0938px;\">References and Bibliography</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 528px; height: 29.0938px;\">They provide a list of authors and papers cited in the report. Be sure to follow the format through the entire paper if you need MLA, Chicago, Harvard, or &nbsp;APA style research report. If you are writing a research report <a title=\"APA Format Citation Machine\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/references-generator/apa-format-citation-machine\">APA Style Free Referencing Tool</a> will be of great use to you.&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>How to Compile a Research Report: Qualitative or Quantitative?</h2>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ve read how to write a research report together with an overview of the structure of research report writing. Note that there are two types of research and research papers and two types of research reports respectively:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualitative Research</li>\r\n<li>Quantitative Research</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you are searching for the information on how to write a qualitative research report, you first need to find out the difference between a qualitative and quantitative research.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Qualitative research</strong> is used to obtain the data such as opinions, thoughts, reasons, etc. It helps ensure the investigation of potential qualitative data.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quantitative research</strong> is aimed to generate numerical data or transform the gathered information into statistics.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>OZessay writing team hopes that you find the above information helpful. Research report writing is a broad topic and in case you need to know more, for example, about report writing research methodology, <a title=\"Place an Order\" href=\"https://www.ozessay.com.au/order\">contact us</a> anytime.&nbsp;</p>','How to Write a Research Report','','publish','closed','closed','','how-to-write-a-research-report','','','2017-07-14 16:03:03','2017-07-14 13:03:03','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(498,1,'2017-07-14 15:55:17','2017-07-14 12:55:17','','how-to-write-a-research-report-ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','how-to-write-a-research-report-ozessay','','','2017-07-14 16:03:03','2017-07-14 13:03:03','',497,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/how-to-write-a-research-report-ozessay.jpg?v=1500037494',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0),(499,1,'2017-09-13 11:16:13','2017-09-13 08:16:13','<h2>What Is Academic Writing?</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Academic writing</strong> is simply known as writing used for academic (educational or scholarly) purposes. This style of writing is used to inform the reader, present results of research or get the reader involved into a scholarly discussion.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Just like other formal styles of writing, it has a set of rules and best practices that must be followed to meet academic standards of writing and to be accepted by the academic community.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here is what makes academic writing different from other writing genres:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Audience</h3>\r\n<p>There are three main audience types that work with academic writing: students, professors (instructors, advisors etc) and professional researchers. Professors give students respective writing assignments while the latter work on them to demonstrate their knowledge and the skills acquired in the writing process. Professional researchers, in turn, generate academic content to talk to fellow scholars, present their research findings and discuss results.</p>\r\n<h3>Background knowledge</h3>\r\n<p>Academic audiences already have some background knowledge about the subject in discussion. Any other audience would have a hard time understanding academic writing that abounds in jargon, professionalisms, and terms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Tone</h3>\r\n<p>The overall writing style should be formal and impersonal. Using impersonal constructions like Passive Voice or speaking from the 3rd person is usually encouraged to ensure objective tone. Please refer to &lsquo;phrases to use in academic writing&rsquo; section of this paper.</p>\r\n<h3>Use of Evidence</h3>\r\n<p>Reference to evidence is another tool that assists academic writers to achieve objectivity and attain. When writing academic papers, an author should refer to objective evidence (research findings, data etc) to sound impersonal and objective.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please refer to the table below for a brief summary of the four distinctive features:</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 96px; width: 722px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 17.5313px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 224px; height: 17.5313px;\"><strong>Audience</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 496px; height: 17.5313px;\">Students, instructors or researchers</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 224px; height: 17px;\"><strong>Background knowledge</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 496px; height: 17px;\">Audience has background knowledge about the subject under discussion</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 224px; height: 17px;\"><strong>Tone</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 496px; height: 17px;\">Formal, impersonal (usually 3d person is used)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 224px; height: 17px;\"><strong>Evidence</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 496px; height: 17px;\">Statements be backed up with research or evidence</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>Table 1.</strong> Distinctive features of the academic style of writing</p>\r\n<h2>Basic Academic Writing Guide from OZessay</h2>\r\n<p>Writing scholarly papers - both for educational and research purposes - requires solid academic writing skills. The good news is that just like muscles, these skills can be built up via exercise. Our concise guide below contains all the basic exercise required for successful academic writing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>NOTE:&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Every university or college will most likely offer their own academic writing guide. These guides are very similar in their essence, yet they differ in the type of detail they contain. Always make sure you obtain and closely follow the writing guide of your institution.</em></p>\r\n<h3>1. Eliminate personal language.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Use of personal pronouns, especially first person, is strongly discouraged. They can make your paper too subjective and we try to avoid that for objectivity reasons.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Example with a </strong>personal<strong> pronoun:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>I believe that&hellip;, I found that&hellip;., we hope that&hellip;, I strongly consider&hellip; etc.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Example:</strong> In this paper, I intend to argue in support of the claim that self-paced learning shows higher efficiency and better results</p>\r\n<p><strong>Example using impersonal language:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>The paper covers the problem of&hellip;, there exists a generally accepted theory that&hellip;, the project focuses on etc.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Example:</strong> The paper will argue in support of the claim that self-paced learning shows higher efficiency and better results.</p>\r\n<h3>2. Use passive voice to maintain objective tone.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><em>It is considered that&hellip;, it is thought that&hellip;, it is argued that&hellip;, the concept of &hellip;. is widespread</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Example:</strong> It will be argued that self-paced learning shows high efficiency and better results.</p>\r\n<h3>3. Relate to your research results, not your feeling/beliefs</h3>\r\n<p><em>The article suggests&hellip;, the data shows that&hellip;, research indicates&hellip;, raw data shows&hellip;, according to&hellip; etc.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Example:</strong> The article by Smith &amp; Johnson (2017) suggests that self-paced learning has higher efficiency and better results compared to conventional learning.</p>\r\n<h2>Phrases to Use and to Avoid in Academic Writing</h2>\r\n<table style=\"height: 110px; width: 722px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.4375px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 386px; height: 13.4375px;\"><strong>Phrases to&nbsp;avoid</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 332px; height: 13.4375px;\"><strong>Phrases to use</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 386px; height: 13px;\">I believe</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 332px; height: 13px;\">It is considered that</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 386px; height: 13px;\">I think</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 332px; height: 13px;\">The results indicate (that)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 386px; height: 13px;\">I am sure that</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 332px; height: 13px;\">Considering the results</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 386px; height: 13px;\">I am convinced that</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 332px; height: 13px;\">According to the figures,&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 386px; height: 13px;\">It is my belief that</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 332px; height: 13px;\">The research indicates/suggests (that)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>Table 1.</strong> Phrases to avoid in academic writing &amp; phrases to use</p>\r\n<h2>How to Write an Academic Essay</h2>\r\n<p>Our website contains information about different types of essays, simple and clear. You can find it easily and use for writing a college paper. And here is a general step by step information on how to write an essay:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Understand the question. If you stuck to the question, consult your instructor for additional explanations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Research your subject. Write a basic outline: make a list of points you would like to write about in your essay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Write a thesis statement. It is a sentence stating the question you would like to expand upon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Write the draft of the essay. Let it be a kind of basis for the final version of your essay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Divide your text into paragraphs: the introductory paragraph, several body paragraphs, and the concluding paragraph.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 6</strong>: Fill your essay with transitional phrases to use in academic writing.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong> Proofread, edit, and write a final draft of your essay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>The Most Common Mistakes in Academic Writing</h2>\r\n<p>Sooner or later, students face the problems with academic writing language. We have put together the most common mistakes in academic writing:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Incorrect sentences. We recommend checking if every sentence you write can stand alone and bear a single complete thought.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Sprawling sentences. Make sure you do not sprawl the sentences as it is hard to read and understand them.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Academic writing connecting words and modifiers. Make sure you use correct connecting words that arrange your thoughts in a logical manner. Place the modifiers near the words and phrases they modify.</li>\r\n<li>Incorrect parallelism. To express 2 or more matching thoughts, use grammatically equal phrases.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Missed commas. Put commas to express the connections between the sentence elements.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Faulty apostrophes. Learn the writing rules of the possessive case of nouns and contractions such as it&rsquo;s, there&rsquo;s and so on.</li>\r\n<li>Confused words. Learn the most confused word in the English language.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Misspelled words. Consult a dictionary if you don&rsquo;t know how to write a particular word.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Can You Learn Fast the Rules of Academic Writing?&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>There are various ways to study academic writing structure and style. You may study thoroughly this type of writing at college or university. You can take IELTS academic writing course; or order some example of academic essay writing from a trusted company and sort every part of the essay out with a professional writer. Feel free to choose any type of studying process you prefer.&nbsp;</p>','Academic Writing','','publish','closed','closed','','academic-writing','','','2017-09-14 11:10:30','2017-09-14 08:10:30','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(500,1,'2017-09-13 11:16:13','2017-09-13 08:16:13','','academic-writing-ozessay','','inherit','closed','closed','','academic-writing-ozessay','','','2017-09-14 11:10:30','2017-09-14 08:10:30','',499,'https://ozessay-a.akamaihd.net/images/article/og/academic-writing-ozessay.jpg?v=1513168612',0,'attachment','image/jpg',0);
